title: celery salmon loaf and sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and pack in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes; turn onto platter.

title: microwave cinnamon nuts
directions: Mix egg white and nuts thoroughly.
Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Add to nuts so egg white absorbs it all.
Place mix in round cake dish.
Cook on power 7 for 6 minutes or until crispy, turning dish at one minute intervals.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Stir in brown sugar, pecans, corn syrup, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
You will not taste the vinegar.
It keeps your pie from boiling over in your stove.

title: mushroom and spinach caesar salad
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms; place in salad bowl. Combine oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour over mushrooms; toss well to coat.
Tear spinach into bite-size pieces.
Add to salad bowl along with croutons, onion and cheese; toss lightly.
Add egg and toss until egg is not visible.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 portions.

title: date cake with broiled frosting(very good)
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Let stand while mixing batter.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add flour and salt alternately with dates mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pan.
As soon as baked, spread with icing mixture and broil until lightly brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Saute onions in margarine.
Mix with sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over potatoes in casserole dish.
Put layer of cheese.
Sprinkle corn flakes over top.
Drizzle margarine over corn flakes.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts and lightly brown.

title: will'o'wisps(kids love these!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip marshmallows in melted butter; roll in cinnamon/sugar.
Wrap marshmallow in crescent roll.
Place in lightly greased muffin tin.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light golden brown.
(Place something under muffin tin in case marshmallows ooze out.)

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a 3-quart microwave container, combine the onion, carrots, oil, garlic and bell and jalapeno peppers.
Cover.
Cook on High 6 to 8 minutes or until the vegetables are softened. Stir once or twice.
Add all of the remaining ingredients except the zucchini. Mix well.
Cover and cook on High 10 minutes and on Medium (50%) for 5 minutes.
Stir in the zucchini.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes on High.
If desired, top individual servings with the low-fat Cheddar cheese.

title: celery au gratin(serves 4 or 5)
directions: Over low heat melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a small saucepan. Blend in flour, dill weed, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Fold cooked celery, chopped peanuts, pimiento and onions into sauce.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Serve immediately.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Grease and flour Bundt cake pan. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done. Cool in pan.

title: mary jacob's sweet pickles
directions: Fill a gallon jug with cucumber slices; add salt.
Finish filling jug with water. Shake well.
Let set 4 days, shaking each day.
At the end of the fourth day, drain off water. Rinse 3 times with cucumbers in jug.
Mix alum with enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse 3 times.
Cover with pure apple vinegar (no water).
Let stand 10 days.
Drain off vinegar (add spices).
Add 3 cups of sugar each day for 3 days (9 cups in all).
Shake each day.
Keep indefinitely.
Do not seal or refrigerate.

title: chicken and pineapple stir-fry
directions: Stir chicken in oil, then add broccoli.
Add ginger, garlic, red pepper and scallions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add pineapple and soy sauce.
Mix 2 teaspoons cornstarch with 2 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Cook until sauce thickens.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix cheese, margarine, flour and Rice Krispies.
Salt and pepper.
Roll in small balls.
Press with fork on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in oven at 350° to 400°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, making sure top is lightly browned.
Stir halfway between cooking.

title: south of the border casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add tomato sauce, chilies and oregano.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes and remove from heat.
In a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 the chips (4 ounces), Monterey Jack cheese, cut in 1/2-inch cubes and beef mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle on Cheddar cheese. Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes to melt cheese.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Stir ingredients just until moist.
Do not overstir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and add all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Cook at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cool yams, peel and slice lengthwise. Place yams in a casserole dish. Sprinkle the raisins over the yams. In a separate bowl, mix the brown sugar, sugar substitute and spices. Sprinkle over yams. Dot with margarine and add cold water. Cover and bake for 30 minutes. Remove the cover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Spread on top of salad.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and shredded cheese.
Chill and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon just before serving.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients and stir in apples, raisins, pecans, coconut and carrots; mix well.
Beat eggs with oil and vanilla; stir into flour mixture until batter is just combined.
Spoon into muffin tins, filling 2/3 full.
Bake muffins in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until springy to the touch.
Makes about 36 muffins.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Add oil to black cast-iron pot over medium heat.
Add flour, slowly stirring until this "roux" is golden brown.
Add chicken to flour mixture (roux) and stir for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and water mixture to 1 gallon of water.
Add seasonings.
Cook over low heat until chicken is tender (approximately 2 hours).
Cut up smoked sausage in 1/2-inch slices and add to chicken and flour mixture. After about 2 hours, add onions and parsley and cook for about 15 minutes longer.
The longer it simmers, the better it tastes.
Then serve over hot rice.
There are hundreds of different gumbo recipes so feel free to experiment and find "your" own.
And don't forget the Tabasco to spice up your life.

title: pineapple stick pops
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and nutmeg. Roll pineapple spears in sugar mixture. Separate crescent rolls. Place a pineapple spear along wide end of triangle; roll to point, folding in sides. Place on cookie sheet; insert wooden skewer. Repeat with remaining rolls. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown; cool. Drizzle with caramel topping; sprinkle with nuts or coconut or both. (This is fun for kids.)

title: chicken over noodles(microwave)
directions: Boil noodles and then drain.
Rinse and place into a casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in microwave for 7 minutes on High.

title: maple syrup
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, sugar and water.
Cook on medium heat to boiling.
Stir until sugars are dissolved.
Add maple flavoring. Makes about 1 cup.

title: minute cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and pecans.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoonsful.
Let cool and serve.

title: jello salad
directions: Add 1 cup hot water to jello.
Set until jiggly, then add cream cheese, half and half and mix together.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put into fridge until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together except for the last two listed.
Pour into glass casserole dish. Sprinkle Ritz crackers over the top and dot with margarine.
Cook 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: nut divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to 242°.
Have white of egg beaten stiff and pour syrup over it.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and place teaspoons at a time on oiled paper.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add chili mix; place hamburger and corn in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread Cheez Whiz on top of hamburger.
In separate bowl, mix cornbread adding corn.
Spread this mixture on top of hamburger mixture and Cheez Whiz.
Bake 425° for 30 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: coney islands
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned; drain.
Add tomato sauce, water, chili powder, paprika and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: brownie cake pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate over hot water in a double boiler.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pie pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then top each serving with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and if desired chocolate sauce.

title: broccoli & rice casserole
directions: Saute' chopped onion in margarine.
Add mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and cooked rice.
Mix together.
Bake 20 - 30 minutes at 350°.

title: catherine's bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine zucchini, onions, and salt.
Mix well and cover with ice cubes.
Let stand for 3-4 hours and then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients into a pot.
Stir well.
Add zucchini, onion, and pepper. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, about 20-30 minutes, until soft.
Pack into hot jars.

title: spicy peach nut bread
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Blend ingredients at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour in pan and bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: pastor's favorite cake mix cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until just turning brown on bottom.
Makes 40 to 50 cookies.

title: no fuss baked chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and mustard in small bowl.
Measure out 1/3 cup and refrigerate.
Brush both sides of chicken with the remaining mixture.
Coat well with the corn flake crumbs.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Add sauce and heat on low. Add soy sauce, vinegar and sugar and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Simmer very low.
Add more soy, vinegar and sugar to taste if needed.
Cook ground beef and drain grease.
Add to sauce and serve on hamburger buns.
For special occasions, substitute roast beef.
Great for an easy holiday buffet.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 7-Up, which is added just before serving.
Add ice cubes and slices of lemon and oranges for decorations.
Serves 12 (4-ounce) glasses.

title: herbed mayonnaise
directions: Combine all in a food processor and puree until smooth.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In saucepan, brown beef; drain.
Add chili, cheese and green chilies.
Heat over medium to low heat, stirring frequently until cheese melts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spray large roaster with Pam and empty corn puffs into it. Cook brown sugar, Karo and oleo in saucepan until it comes to a boil.
Remove mixture from heat and add baking soda.
Stir until dissolved.
Mixture will foam up a little.
Pour mixture over puffs a little at a time.
Toss and coat well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Toss every 15 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients.

title: nutritious low-fat blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray or use paper cups.
Combine flours, salt and baking powder. In a separate bowl, combine oil, sugar, egg whites and milk.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and mix together.
Stir berries lightly into the batter.
Spoon the batter into muffin tin.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Thaw berries and mash into a glass 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour in Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Add Cool Whip.
Freeze and serve.
Easy and good!!

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Cut 6 slices of cheese into pieces; set aside.

title: chicken and rice milanese
directions: Simmer chicken in water with seasonings, celery, parsley and onion until tender.
Strain and reserve stock.
Bone chicken and leave in nice pieces.
Brown rice in margarine until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add chicken stock and simmer.
While rice is simmering, add all the ingredients, one by one, as you get them prepared.
Last, add the boned chicken.
Mix well and pour into a large casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
It should be juicy and moist.
If somewhat dry, add more chicken broth or spaghetti sauce.
Serves

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine tapioca, jello and pudding mix with water; cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Will burn easily.
When cool, mix with topping and drained oranges.
(Drained juice may be used as part of water.)
Serves 8 or 9.
Goes great with ham or roast.

title: choco-caramel pecan pie
directions: In medium mixing bowl, stir together softened ice cream, crushed cookies and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into Keebler pie crust and freeze until firm.
While this is freezing, mix together cream cheese and caramel topping in medium mixing bowl with electric mixer on low speed until creamy.
Spread cream cheese/caramel mixture over frozen ice cream mixture, then carefully spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Return to freezer until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix flour, shortening and enough cold water to make a stiff dough.
Divide dough in half and roll out thin.
Spread each half with 2 cups apples and roll up.
Repeat with other half.
Put rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to boil in a pan the white sugar, brown sugar, water and margarine.
Pour this over the rolls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Dip liquid on pastry once or twice while baking.

title: frozen sweet corn
directions: *Corn should be very ripe.

title: english toffee
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it melt the 1 cup butter.
Add sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat to 290° (soft crack stage), stirring frequently (mixture should boil gently over entire surface).
Watch carefully after 280°.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in the 1/2 cup coarsely chopped nuts.
Immediately turn into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Wait 2 to 3 minutes for toffee surface to firm, then sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes.
When chocolate is softened, spread evenly over toffee; sprinkle with the finely chopped nuts.
Chill until chocolate is firm; break into pieces. Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and baking soda. Set aside.
Blend vanilla, oil and sugars together.
Add egg whites and blend well.
Stir in flour, oatmeal and nuts.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Drop dough onto cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Makes 72.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Peel potatoes; cut in finger-size pieces. Place in casserole; sprinkle with remaining ingredients. Bake, covered, for 45 to 50 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix; pour in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with miniature marshmallows; cook until brown.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Heat every ingredient for about 20 minutes.
Strain the spices and serve hot.

title: jude's cincinnati empress chili
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a skillet.
Add pinch of sugar and remaining ingredients and cook over slow heat with 1 quart of water and Worcestershire to taste.
Cook a minimum of 1 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine avocados and tomato; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; blend thoroughly.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in peelings until not quite done.
Peel and grate after cooling.
Grate cheese and add to potatoes.
Saute onions in 1/4 cup butter.
Add sour cream and soup to onions.
Mix together with potatoes and cheese.
Put mixture in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Top with crushed cornflakes, mixed with melted butter. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute the onion and almonds in margarine and add to rest of ingredients in a large casserole dish. Cover top with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke-crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spoon into lightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with assorted crackers.

title: scottish shortbread (scotland)
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla and cream well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Knead a few times on very lightly floured board.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Score with fork or imprint with a fancy design. Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 20 to 30 minutes or until delicately brown.

title: sausage and potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine soup, milk, chopped onion and green pepper, blending well.
Layer potatoes and sausage in 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup mixture over each layer; sprinkle with cheese.
Dot with margarine.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onion in butter or oil.
Add seasonings and chicken. Brown 10 minutes.
Add water.
Cover and let simmer slowly until tender.
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to drippings in pan and mix well.
Add dumplings.
Arrange chicken on top.
Heat through and serve.

title: sherry crab casserole
directions: Break crab meat into chunks.
In a casserole, layer 1/2 of crab meat, 1/2 of peas, 1/2 of mushrooms and 1/2 of pimentos. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.

title: congealed pear salad
directions: Make jello by directions on box.
While jello is cooling, mix nuts, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fill pear halves with mixture. Put in oblong deep dish.
When jelly is cool, pour over the pears.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Cut each half separate and serve on lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Let boil 5 minutes and place pan in cool water. Beat until desired consistency.

title: play dough for children
directions: Combine all ingredients
in saucepan over medium heat; mix well.
Cook, stirring until the mixture sticks together and forms a large ball.
Pour into waxed paper.
Let cool.
Store in a covered container until children are ready to play with it.
Makes 2 cups.

title: beef teriyaki and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and seasonings.
Add beef strips; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Mash and add all ingredients, except cheese.
Mix.
Put into a 1-quart baking dish with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Melt Crisco in a large iron skillet.
Roll chicken in flour. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Fry for 20 minutes on each side. Cook on medium-high until brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Grease or spray pans.
Beat egg whites, whipping cream, 2 1/2 cups sugar and water.
Slowly add flour beating as you go.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Grate coconut after taking milk.
Use milk from coconut, add with 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar (having about 3/4 cup altogether).
Bring to boil long enough to dissolve sugar.
Slowly drizzle over layers.
Make fluffy white frosting. Frost cake; cover with grated coconut.
Use 9-inch pans.

title: substitute adelphi bologna
directions: Mix together well.
Roll in lengths with plastic wrap, then refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove plastic wrap and bake in a shallow pan at 300° for one hour.
While still warm, pat off excess fat with paper towels.
Cool before slicing.

title: "jewish style" potato pancakes(latkes)
directions: Peel and grate potatoes (blender may be used).
Grate onion into potatoes.
Add eggs, matzo meal, salt, pepper and garlic to make a smooth batter (fairly heavy like pancake mix).
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and brown in deep frying pan.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix in pan and heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: layered enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off any excess grease. Add salt, pepper, chili powder and olives.
Mix tomato sauce and enchilada sauce together.
Add 1/2 of the sauce to meat mixture. Mix well.
Lightly spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and all 10 tortillas (both sides).
Put 3 1/3 tortillas on bottom of casserole, 1/3 meat mixture on top of tortillas, then 1/3 of shredded cheese, then 1/3 of Velveeta cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat this 2 more times, ending with Velveeta. Pour remaining sauce over top and sides of casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in casserole dish and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325° or 350°.

title: no bake peanut butter bites
directions: Combine butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Frost with melted chocolate.
Let frosting set at room temperature, then cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cauliflower
directions: Peel outside leaves and stem from cauliflower.
Place in pan and steam until tender.
Take from pan and put on a casserole dish and spread with mayonnaise.
Place under broiler until brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut in slices and serve.

title: sophia loren's pizza
directions: Mix dough according to directions.
Place on waxed paper covered with cornmeal.
Knead meal into dough.
Roll out. Reserve 2 tablespoons olive oil and use the rest to oil the pan. Place dough on pan.
Spread remaining oil on top.
Spread on the sauce.
Put on remaining ingredients, spreading the cheese last. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken with black beans
directions: Rinse black beans; mash and mix with garlic.
Heat oil.
Add bean mixture and saute for 1 minute.
Add chicken and saute.
Add salt and onion.
Cover and cook until almost done.
Add green peppers, cornstarch and oyster sauce.
Cover and simmer until done.

title: gingered chinese noodle soup
directions: Put noodles in a large bowl.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Heat oil in wok or deep large skillet over medium high heat.
Add onion and carrots; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add garlic and ginger; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add stock, water and soy sauce.
Cover and boil 2 minutes.
Add ham, watercress, mushrooms and noodles.
Return to boil.
Cover; turn off heat and let steep until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in sesame oil, rice vinegar and red pepper flakes. Adjust seasoning to taste.
Serve in deep bowls; sprinkle with green onions.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg and add to milk.
Mix with the dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of meat or chicken stew.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes without removing the cover.

title: fudge
directions: Combine the cocoa, salt and sugar. Stir in the milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat until soft-ball stage. Remove from heat; add oleo and vanilla. Do not stir. Cool to room temperature. Beat with wooden spoon for 10 minutes. Pour in a square pan; let set, then cut into squares.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Put all ingredients (except Rice Krispies and nuts) in thick boiler, turn on heat; let cook 6 minutes, stirring all the time. Then add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Let cool and roll into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Can be frozen well, if packed in tight container.

title: spread for toast or chips
directions: Mix well and serve with toast or chips.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put in crock-pot in this order. Do not stir. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or on high 4 to 6 hours. Do not lift lid or stir during cooking.
Makes 12 cups.

title: red wine stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours in a covered casserole.
Serve over wild rice.

title: rave review cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; blend and beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir coconut and nuts.
Pour into a greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: loaded carrot cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients then add last 4 ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: andrew's famous instant oatmeal
directions: Empty envelope into a bowl.
Add boiling water and stir.
Add ice cubes (to cool).
Let stand 1 minute.

title: to can coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, peppers and salt in a large bowl.
Cover with ice water.
Cover container.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain well and pack lightly in sterilized jars.

title: "rice" pudding
directions: After rice has cooked, mix all the ingredients.
Bake in 400° oven 45 minutes or until middle is firm.

title: coconut milk cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed in two 9-inch round cake pans. Poke holes in cake.
Mix can of condensed milk and coconut milk together and pour over cake while still warm and let stand until mixture is absorbed in the cake.
When cool, cover cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle cake with coconut.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix all other items together.
Place pork chops in baking pan and pour mixture over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: Cook chicken in oil over medium heat about 15 minutes, until brown.
Drain.
Mix sauce for tacos, water, salt, oregano, instant garlic and instant onion.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Place chicken in an ungreased 9 x 9-inch baking pan or in ovenproof serving dish. Cool.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Heat at 400°.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots and drain; cool.
Combine last five items and bring to boil; pour over carrots, onions and green peppers.
Let stand overnight.

title: cherry delight
directions: Drain pineapple and mix pineapple, cream cheese, cherry pie filling, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk altogether.
Refrigerate.

title: buttermilk gravy
directions: Fry fat back.
Leave 4 tablespoons grease in skillet. Stir in cornmeal and flour. Brown.
Add buttermilk and stir until it boils. Serve over cornbread or fried potatoes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine eggs and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cut toast in small pieces.
Stir toast, salt, cinnamon, liquid Butter Buds and raisins into egg mixture.
Pour into a shallow 2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Set the baking dish into a larger shallow pan. Pour hot water into larger pan to depth of 1-inch.
Bake for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim excess fat from around steak.
Pound flour into both sides of steak; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet; add steak and brown well over medium heat.
Place steak in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In the drippings in the skillet, lightly cook onion, celery, mushrooms and garlic.
Stir in tomatoes, basil, oregano and thyme.
Pour over steak.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour in shell. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: boiled rice pudding
directions: Boil rice with salt until soft.
Add 2 cups milk and sugar. Let come to boil.
Add egg and vanilla.
As soon as it comes to a boil, add cornstarch and 3/4 cup milk (which has been shaken together in a shaker) and boil until thick, stirring constantly. Eat warm or cold.

title: golden cheese soup
directions: Simmer vegetables and seasonings in water just until tender. Blend milk and flour.
Add vegetables and cook until thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted.
Do not overcook.

title: overnight caramel rolls
directions: Place nuts in the bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan.
Place rolls on top of the nuts.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix on the rolls. Melt together the butter and the brown sugar and then drizzle over pudding mix.
Let stand overnight to thaw and rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lacy's teacakes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except flour together. Measure out 4 cups flour and add gradually until the dough is the right consistency to roll. Do not make dough too dry. Roll the dough out thin and cut in desired shapes. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes. Sprinkle sugar on top of each teacake.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Saut onions in melted butter for 10 minutes in large kettle. Add flour and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring until flour is absorbed. In separate container, combine water, bouillon, flakes and seasonings. Stir until thoroughly mixed and no lumps remain. Add to onion mixture 1 pt. at a time. Add milk and cream, stirring until smooth and lightly thickened. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. In separate container, potatoes should be brought to a boil and simmered 20 minutes. Add potatoes to soup mixture to complete.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Fry spareribs in oil until brown.
Add ginger and garlic.
Mix sugar, salt, shoyu, vinegar and water; pour over spareribs.
Cook for at least 1 hour on low heat or until spareribs are soft. Thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch.
If gravy begins to lessen, add more water as you are cooking so not to burn the spareribs.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugars, vanilla and mustard.
Stir in milk.
Gently fold in potatoes, eggs, celery, radishes, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve in a bowl lined with lettuce leaves. Sprinkle paprika and parsley on top.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Layer in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham-chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice; cook broccoli.
Spread rice in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Add broccoli, ham or chicken and cheese.
Add blended cheese soup with mayonnaise, mustard and curry.
Spread over all.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes
in 350° oven.

title: brown sugar crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Keep 1 cup for topping.
To the remainder, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle the 1 cup reserved mix for topping over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Combine peanut butter, vanilla and flour to mixture. Roll cookies into a ball and mash with a fork for a crisscross pattern. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed meat loaf rolls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Combine with remaining ingredients except cheese and catsup.
On a sheet of waxed paper, spread meat mixture to form a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and roll up like a jelly roll.
Place seam side down in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart glass loaf pan.
Bake meat loaf uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cover with catsup and cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: orange spice buns
directions: Thaw dough according to package directions.
On a lightly floured surface, pat or roll dough into a 12 x 6-inch rectangle. (If dough is difficult to roll, let it rest for 10 minutes for easier handling.)
Cut crosswise into twelve 6 x 1-inch strips. With your fingers, stretch each strip to 10 inches long.

title: texas crunch
directions: Boil brown sugar and butter for mix. Do not stir! Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Place one layer of crackers on cookie sheet. Pour sugar mixture on crackers. Bake at 350 degrees for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips and peanut butter chips on crackers. Cool 10 minutes. Swirl with fork covering all crackers well. Refrigerate; when cold pull apart.

title: aunt lena and aunt pat's cheese cake
directions: Combine and pour into graham cracker lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool 15 minutes.
Combine 1 pint sour cream, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Chill.
Use any topping or plain.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Soften cream cheese, add mayonnaise, sour cream and Parmesan cheese; make creamy.
Chop artichoke hearts.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add garlic and dill.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with jumbo corn chips.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Add ice and Sprite or Seven-Up to taste.

title: beans, beans, beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Mix beans in 5-quart Dutch oven. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put 3 cups water in a saucepan with the orange peel, cinnamon stick and salt until boiled.
When starts boiling, add rice (rice must be washed).
Put top on saucepan and let rice boil under low flames (until dried).

title: mixed nut crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large shallow roasting pan or two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans, spread popcorn and nuts.
In a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove. Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Cool.
Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: syrup cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in syrup, grease, eggs and milk.
Pour in flat pan and bake.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Add meat to oil and brown for 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green pepper strips last 5 minutes. While meat simmers, cook rice.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture until thickened; heat through.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla slowly. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat temperature to 325° and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot artichoke crab dip
directions: Combine artichoke hearts, mayo, crab meat, cheese and garlic powder in medium bowl, stirring well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole. Cover with wax paper and microwave on Medium (50%) for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated thoroughly, rotating a half turn after 3 minutes, if microwave does not have a turn table. Sprinkle with parsley and paprika. Serve immediately with crackers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook syrup until it spins a thread.
Turn off heat; add soda. Mix well.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Butter your hands and form popcorn balls.

title: grossmommy's rolls
directions: Melt
yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar. Combine 2 cups flour with other dry ingredients.
Add eggs and yeast mixture.
Knead.
Let rise until double;
punch down and let rise
again.
Make
rolls.
Bake on greased baking sheets for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: quick dish dinner
directions: Dice the bacon; cook in a large skillet until crisp.
Crumble in ground beef and brown well; drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, slightly breaking up tomatoes and dampening macaroni.
Cover and simmer gently for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pot pie(low calorie, low cholesterol)
directions: In a 9-inch nonstick skillet, melt margarine, add vegetables and saute over medium heat until carrot is tender-crisp.
Add chicken and stir to combine.
Sprinkle flour over vegetable mixture and stir quickly to combine; cook 1 minute.
Continuing to stir, add broth gradually and bring to a boil.
Reduce to low and let simmer until thickened (5 minutes).

title: jello dessert
directions: Combine orange jello, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows. Add reserved juice, plus water, to make 1 cup.
Let jello get firm.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Add other ingredients (except tortillas and grated cheese).
Cut tortillas into quarters.
Spoon some meat mixture into casserole followed by a layer of tortillas and then cheese.
Repeat until all meat mixture is used ending with meat on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tropical ice(for diabetics)
directions: Combine orange juice, bananas, pineapple, lemon juice and sugar substitute in a large mixing bowl.
Freeze until firm.

title: oatmeal sheet cake
directions: Put oats in 2 cup hot water; let set in water until other ingredients are mixed.
Fold oats in last.
Bake in slow oven at about 325° until done.
Bake in wide loaf pan.
Let cool.
Spread topping on and broil to desired crispness.

title: hash brown oven omelet
directions: Brown onions and green pepper in butter.
Spread hash browns on bottom of a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle meat over hash browns. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over potatoes. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
(This works great if it is covered and refrigerated overnight and baked in the morning.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until it is thick, then add Cool Whip and sour cream. Make layers. Refrigerate.

title: chinese stew
directions: Slice meat thin and sprinkle with pepper.
Brown meat in oil. Add golden mushroom soup, water, onion and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add cabbage, cut into 1-inch pieces and bamboo shoots or Chinese vegetables.
Simmer, covered, for 8 minutes or until cabbage is done.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6. Cooking time is 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Combine eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Spray 12 cup muffin tin with nonstick spray.
Fill and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Two servings (6 each) = 1 bread, 1 protein, 1 milk and 1 fruit.

title: c~b's brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken and remove skin and bones (dice in small pieces). Prepare stew beef to your taste. Remove ham and return chicken and stew beef to ham stock (reserve chicken and beef stock). Add all vegetables except cream-style corn (if more liquids are needed, use chicken or beef stock). Add cream-style corn when vegetables are done. Add a pinch of sugar.

title: spiced apple muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg; blend well.
Add milk alternately with sifted mixture of flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in apples.
Fill greased muffin pans half full, then top with topping mixture.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in the 1 1/2 sticks oleo.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix the regular corn kit, Mexicorn kit, eggs, milk and cottage cheese. Add sauteed mixture.
Pour in buttered pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Remove from heat and beat 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil together, then combine other ingredients and stir.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot-rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar. Let stand overnight. Boil for 10 minutes, then add pie filling and lemon juice. Bring mixture to a boil and add the Jell-O. Stir until Jell-O dissolves. Pour into jelly jars and seal. You can also use strawberry pie filling and strawberry Jell-O.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Melt margarine in 10
x
15-inch
Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle graham crumbs over margarine.
Add a layer of coconut, a layer of fruit and a layer
of
dates.
Sprinkle
pecans over dates. Press mixture lightly with hand
to
level
it
in
the
pan. Drizzle milk over top and bake
for
about 30 minutes or until lightly brown at 325°.
Do	not
overbake.	Allow
to get cold and cut into 2-inch squares or strips.

title: vernon's barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: company green beans
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes.
Add parsley, rosemary and basil; simmer, covered, 5 minutes.

title: curried hot fruit medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange fruit in a 2 quart baking dish.
Combine butter, sugar, curry powder and salt in a small saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.	Serve hot topped with a dollop of sour cream, if desired.	Serves 6-8.

title: my favorite cheesecake
directions: Whip together cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust and chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Add cherries, if desired.

title: cabbage and dumplings
directions: Put 4 cups water and ham on to boil. Shred cabbage and put in boiling water. Cook 1/2 to 1 hour or until cabbage is tender. Add vinegar and salt. Mix flour, eggs, baking powder and salt with enough water to moisten. Spoon on top of cooking cabbage. Cover and cook about 15 minutes or until dumplings are cooked when cut in half. Grate potato. Take dumplings out and put grated potatoes in cabbage to thicken. "Enjoy."

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in a large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.

title: italian lasagne
directions: Brown sausage and beef.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, paste and olive oil.
Bring to boil and simmer slowly while preparing remainder of recipe.

title: lifestyle praying
directions: Begin
each
day
by combining a generous amount of all ingredients.
Mix
well at the same time and in the same place every
day.
Stir
continuously,
throughout
the day, without ceasing.
Cook according to His will.
Serve in His name.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes, making sure it's mixed well.
Grease 2 large loaf pans and pour in mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt thoroughly.
Add milk slowly. Cook in top
of double boiler over hot water until thick.
Put in lemon juice
and	rind.
Cook
a	few
minutes more and add margarine. Cool.
Place
in
deep
dish baked pie shell. Whip egg whites
by hand until stiff.
Beat in sugar slowly.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ma-ma's icebox cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly and roll into 4 to 5 sticks , wrapping each stick in waxed paper.
Freezer or refrigerate.
Slice in about 1/4-inch slices.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 1 1/2-quart bowl, put in flour, margarine and salt.
Mix with pastry blender or 2 knives until coarse.
With back of spoon, press mixture firmly onto bottom and halfway up sides of buttered 8-inch square pan.
Drain peaches well, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Arrange peaches on crust in pan. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture; bake 20 minutes.
Mix reserved syrup, evaporated milk and egg, slightly beaten; pour over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes more or until custard is firm, except in center.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 9.

title: boiling water crust 2
directions: Place shortening and milk in a large heatproof bowl.
Pour in boiling water and whisk until mixture is the consistency of heavy cream.
In a medium bowl, mix together flour and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Mix with a wooden spoon just until dough forms a ball.
Refrigerate before rolling out.
Makes 1 double crust (8 servings).

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli per pkg. instructions.
Add eggs, onions, soup, and mayonnaise to make a sauce.
In a casserole dish put down a layer of broccoli, a layer of cheese, and cover in a small amount of sauce.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle the stuffing mix on top, and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: koloche(slavic christmas roll)
directions: Mix flour and butter as for pie crust.
Add beaten egg yolks, crumbled yeast, salt, sugar and sour cream.
Mix together lightly. Cover bowl with damp towel and put in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, divide into 3 or 4 pieces and roll out on board with powdered sugar and roll very thin.
Cut in 3-inch squares and fill with nut mixture ( recipe follows).
Roll each square as for jelly roll.
Place on cookie sheet about 1/2 inch apart and brush with egg whites.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and place shallow layer in baking dish.
Cover with Doritos.
Alternate layers with mixture and Doritos chips. Place in oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk to a boil.
Pour over mixture of oatmeal, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Stir thoroughly and drop on wax paper until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not drain whole kernel corn. Put into casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, uncovered.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients, except buttermilk, in a bowl and mix well.
Add buttermilk and beat 15 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into well-greased pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: swedish baked rice pudding
directions: Simmer rice, water and salt for 15 minutes.
Drain, if necessary.
In separate pan, cook until thick: egg yolks, milk, sugar and cornstarch.
Add rice to pudding mixture and stir together well.
Beat egg whites with a little white sugar and spread on top of rice.
Bake in a 375° oven until egg whites are golden brown.
Remove from oven and allow to cool about 15 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.

title: peach tart
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and milk.
Put peaches in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Dot top of shell with butter. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°.
Bake another 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together shortening and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Mix in oats and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: coq au vin rouge (chicken in red wine)
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; season and brown in hot oil.
When browned, drain on brown paper or paper towels.
Put in deep pot (crock-pot if you have one).
Pour approximately 3/4 cup wine over.
Cover and cook approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add more wine to taste and serve with mashed/baked potatoes or fluffy rice. Can be prepared a day ahead.
The drunker the chicken, the better!

title: no bake drop cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and cocoa. Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Mix quick oats, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Drop by spoon onto buttered cookie sheet. Allow to cool.

title: cry babies(cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto greased sheet and bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.
Ice with a powdered sugar icing while cookies are still warm.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Boil eggplant in salted water until tender.
Drain thoroughly, then add margarine and mash.
Add onion.
Add bread with milk to mixture.
Add egg yolks and salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into eggplant mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Cook 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: bacon cheese appetizers
directions: Slice bacon in half.
Cut cheese in 16 even cubes.
Sprinkle cheese cubes with cayenne pepper.
Wrap bacon slices around cheese cubes; use wooden toothpicks to hold together.
Place on oven pan. Cook for 3 minutes on broil, then turn over and cook for 3 minutes on other side.
Remove from oven.
Put sliced cherry tomato halves on other end of toothpick with bacon and cheese.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken (season).
Debone chicken and set aside.
Saute green pepper and onions in skillet; set aside.
Cook egg noodles or spaghetti in boiling chicken broth.
After noodles are done, add 1 can mushroom soup.
(Additional mushrooms can be added, if desired.)

title: apricot bars
directions: In
large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.

title: broccoli-tomato chicken
directions: Season
chicken with salt and pepper.
In a medium-size frying pan,
melt margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken and onion and cook until chicken is opaque, about 8 minutes.
Add broccoli, lemon
juice,
thyme
and
salt and pepper to taste. Add tomatoes and simmer, covered, 3 to 4 minutes, until hot.

title: hanky-pankies
directions: Brown beef and sausage together.
Drain.
Add oregano (to taste).
Add cheese and melt; spread on bread and brown under broiler.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and almond extract.
Pour into spring-form pan. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven.
Cool for 20 minutes. Mix sour cream, remaining sugar (2 tablespoons) and vanilla.
Pour over cheese cake.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring water to a boil and steep tea bags for 5 minutes. Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: potato casserole with cheese
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain well and mash. Add margarine, cream cheese, chives and a little milk, if desired. Put in buttered casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: mock tacos
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and black olives.
Spread thin coating of mixture on a tortilla.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Add a thin layer of ham.
Roll the tortilla and wrap in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Continue process until cream cheese mixture is used.
Cut into 1-inch slices to serve.

title: tomato salad
directions: In a bowl, whisk together vinegar, oil, garlic, oregano, basil, sugar, salt and pepper. Add onion and green pepper. Toss to coat. Stir in tomatoes, olives and cheese. Cover and refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Cut in small wedges.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Add salt and pepper, margarine and soup.
Bring to boil.
Add cold milk.
Bring to slight boil and turn off.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve soda in milk; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 1 cup mini morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla, stirring just until blended.
(Do not overbeat).

title: sweet corn chowder with shrimp and red peppers
directions: Heat oil for 1 minute in large saucepan over moderate heat. Add onion and saute, stirring until limp, about 5 minutes.
Add potato, bay leaf, marjoram, nutmeg and stock.
Bring to boil until potato is just tender, about 10 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix flour with baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Combine milk and beaten eggs.
Beat the 2 mixtures together well.
Then stir in chopped apples.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot fat (as for doughnuts).
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 15.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix ingredients well in large bowl.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with large tortilla chips.
Great party dip for a large group.

title: hot diggity dogs
directions: Slice hot dog in half, but not all the way through.
Insert cheese in hot dog.
Wrap the biscuit around the hot dog and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until the biscuit browns slightly.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on bottom of pie plate. Pour on sauce.
Garnish with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: quick casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside. Saute ground chuck and onions. Combine remaining ingredients together. Heat and add to meat mixture. Spread noodles in a 3-quart casserole dish; cover with meat mixture. Sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese over this. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes. Remove and top with cashew nuts (optional) or 1 can Chinese chow mein noodles. Place in oven for 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate sauce(yield: 1 cup)
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar.
Heat milk and margarine.
Slowly add cocoa-sugar mixture, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil, add vanilla.
Mixture will thicken as it cools.
Serve over low-fat/nonfat frozen yogurt or angel food cake.

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add corn; simmer 5 minutes.
Add milk and cheese; stir until cheese melts and chowder is heated through.
Do not boil.

title: forget the diet frozen dessert
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are well blended.
Add granulated	sugar
and
salt.
Beat
in
evaporated
milk
and vanilla.
Sprinkle brown
sugar
into
bottom
of	loaf
pan. Gently pour custard
mixture over brown sugar.
Place loaf pan in shallow baking
pan
containing hot water.	Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Refrigerate overnight.
Before
serving, run knife around edge of pan and turn out onto small platter.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Combine oil and butter over medium heat.
Pound chicken between layers of Saran Wrap.
Dredge chicken in flour/herb mixture and shake off excess.
Saute for 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Add mushrooms and Marsala wine.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Recipe can be doubled.

title: quick apple tarts
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and salt. Gradually stir in flour until soft dough is formed.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cheddar-cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Add sifted flour, salt and paprika; mix well.
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive to cover.
At this point, you may refrigerate or freeze cheese puffs for up to 10 days.
Bake puffs at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: slice of heaven pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 oz. almond bark in 2 quart bowl on HI for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave 1-2 minutes more until smooth when stirred.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour into greased 12 inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle coconut on top.
Microwave remaining 2 oz. almond bark and oil in measuring cup for 1 minute.
Stir until smooth; drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into wedges.
Makes about 16 pieces.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and keep hot.

title: spinach-stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Trim fat from chicken and discard. Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of plastic wrap. Pound with meat mallet until chicken is about 1/4-inch thick. Preheat oven to 350°. Pat spinach dry with paper towels. Combine spinach, Parmesan cheese, lemon peel and black pepper in large bowl. Spray small nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Add mushrooms; cook and stir over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.

title: ann landers meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix meats together by hand in large bowl.
Add Worcestershire sauce, eggs, cracker crumbs, catsup, water and soup mix.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Drape loaf with bacon strips.
Then pour tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese over bottom of pie crust in pan.
Beat eggs; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture over bacon and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press evenly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: crescents
directions: Cream butter well in mixer; add sugar.
Cream well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Add pecans.
Shape as crescents or in little round balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until tops are slightly light brown.
While cookies are baking, spread several paper towels on surface on which to sift 1/2 package confectioners sugar.
Carefully take up cookies and place on confectioners sugar.
Then sift remaining confectioners sugar over tops of hot cookies.
Cool.
Lightly press cookies over sugar as you take them up to place in cookie tin.

title: stuffed peppers, tomatoes and potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dig hole inside vegetables after slicing the top.
Spoon in mixture.
Leave excess cut out vegetables in pan.
After filling, put tops on.
Baste often during cooking. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sour cream and stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pastry shell and top with regular or lattice top crust.
Sprinkle with more nutmeg if desired.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: grilled sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Saute onion and green pepper 3 minutes. Mix together cornstarch, sugar, vinegar, broth and salt. Add to the saucepan, stirring steadily to the boiling point.
Add the pickles and pineapple. Cook over low heat 3 minutes.
Place ribs on heavy aluminum foil tray on grill over low coals. Cook slowly with grill hood closed, turning and basting ribs with sauce frequently.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mushroom green beans
directions: Pour green beans in a small casserole dish.
Add spices and stir.
Pour soup over top and cover green beans.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except chips and nuts.
Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce, tomatoes and onion as for tossed salad.
Add the chilled Ranch Style beans.
Just before serving, add the grated cheese, crushed Fritos and Catalina dressing.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix well.
Divide into thirds.
Place in plastic bags and refrigerate for 3 days, kneading about 3 times a day in the bags. On the 4th day, place formed salami on a broiler pan, bake in oven at 150° for 9 to 9 1/2 hours.

title: bourbon beans
directions: Mix beans, coffee and bourbon.
Place in casserole.
Stand pineapple halves around edges.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, and pour into well greased iron skillet. Bake in 350 degree oven until done and golden brown.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, dash of pepper and 1/4 cup tomato soup.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and place in baking dish.
Mix remaining soup with water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix spices together.
An electric blender may be used to blend spices more finely.
Sprinkle in small amounts over meat.
Add water.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 24 hours, kneading once. Knead again and shape into 5 rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Place on rack of broiling pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours, turning once.
Cook and refrigerate.

title: raita
directions: Put yogurt in bowl.
Mix with fork to make it smooth.
Grate cucumber in a small bowl.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Blend into yogurt.
Add salt, dill and mint.
Put into refrigerator for at least an hour or two.
Sprinkle dill on top before serving.

title: elise's super sweaty salsa
directions: Place all ingredients (except cilantro and oregano) in the blender or food processor. Puree on medium setting for about 10 seconds, or until smooth. Pour into serving bowl. Stir in cilantro and oregano. Let sit for a 30 minutes before serving. Serves 12.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients together in a buttered casserole dish.
Add the peas and mix.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Through cheesecloth, strain juice into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with plastic wrap; freeze until solid.
When ready to serve, chop granita with metal spatula or metal pastry scraper.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet; salt and pepper.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chops on potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: furr's jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cornmeal.
Add egg, oil and buttermilk.
Blend in well the remaining ingredients. Pour into miniature loaf pans.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done in center.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into marble size balls and flatten with fork.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan onto wax paper or paper sacks.

title: crab melts
directions: Process crabmeat in food processor until chopped well. Combine crabmeat, melted butter, mayo, cheese, garlic salt and seasoned salt; mix well.
Spread mixture on cocktail bread.
Place on baking sheets and bake at 350° until bubbly.
(Can do ahead; can freeze.)

title: apple pie
directions: Wash and prepare fruit.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into "Mom's Pie Crust".
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover with top crust, flute edges and prick top with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry-cream squares
directions: Dissolve strawberry-flavored gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple and bananas (also nuts).
Pour half into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or mold.
Chill until firm.
Spread evenly with dairy sour cream. Pour remaining gelatin atop.
Chill until firm.

title: dill dip
directions: Serve with Fritos corn chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: moon cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: sugar and spice coffee cake
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 round greased and floured cake pans; sprinkle with the reserved 1/2 cup of mixture for topping.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until browned.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and heat well. Serve over a roast that has been pressure cooked until it falls apart and has been cut up into bite size pieces. Serve as a main dish or on buns as sandwiches.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix ingredients together until crumbly.
Put 3/4 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rhubarb mixture over this, then add remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cousin clara's bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Slice onion, celery and pepper thinly. Mix beans, onion, celery and pepper together.

title: easy chicken enchilada soup
directions: Mix and warm to boil.

title: baked fudge squares
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add sugar; beat.
Add eggs; beat. Add flour, nuts and vanilla; beat.
Bake in well-greased pan at 375° for 25 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut in squares (or pie-shape wedges) to serve with ice cream.
Do not overbake.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix butter, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed and onion; set aside.

title: cranberry-apple relish for microwave
directions: Add cranberries, apples and nuts after cooking relish. Microwave 9 to 11 minutes until skins break and liquid is slightly thickened.
Stir halfway through, 6 minutes.
Finish cooking and stir in walnuts.
Cool and refrigerate; will become thicker.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Bring to a boil all of the above ingredients.
Let set.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all together and bake 3 hours at 325°.
Serve with hot bread and enjoy.

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from all peppers.
Combine vegetables and cover with cold water.
Cook 5 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: no fire s'mores
directions: Split graham crackers into halves. Place mini marshmallows on top of crackers. Put under broiler for a few seconds, until toasty. Remove from broiler and put 1/2 piece of chocolate on top of marshmallows. Put another half of cracker on top of chocolate and press gently down to flatten marshmallows.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In large mixing bowl mix butter, sour cream and sugar until smooth.
Add sweet potato puree and eggs.
Mix until incorporated. Add vanilla, then fold in dry ingredients.
Pour the mixture into a lightly oiled 9-inch loaf pan and bake in 300° oven for 45 to 55 minutes until a toothpick or skewer inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove from oven.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: quiche
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix all ingredients except meat and cheese.
Pour in deep pie pan.
Drop in meat and sprinkle cheese on top; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: This is a luscious mousse, served with a vanilla bean white cream sauce, straight from Paris, France!

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches; dot with butter.

title: coffee orange fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch fluted tube pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, eggs, pudding mix, liquor, orange peel and cinnamon.
Beat with mixer on low speed until blended, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces.

title: sugar cookie fruit tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 in fluted tart pan with removable bottom. Press cookie dough in bottom. Bake 22 mins. Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread over cookie crust. Arrange fruit on top and chill for 1 hr.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll in chopped pecans. Garnish with pecan halves on top of rolled ball.
Refrigerate at least 1 day ahead.
Yield: 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: shrimp boil
directions: This is a fun meal that requires very little effort. Place the potatoes in a large pot a boiling water along with the crab boil. When the potatoes are almost done drop in the chopped up sausages, and the
corn.
WARNING the corn will absorb the crab boil and if left in very long
will be VERY SPICY, so it's best to use precooked frozen corn, if you insist
on fresh, cook the corn in a separate pot before adding it to the crab boil.
When everything is almost done drop in the shrimp. Cook until they turn pink.
Drain off the water and dump into a huge bowl, serve with butter, cocktail
sauce and lots of napkins. Want a real seafood feast, try adding crawfish, king crab legs and lobster to
the boil.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk, butter, soda and 1/2 cup cocoa thoroughly. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: y. o. ranch
directions: Bake at 475° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue meat
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until well done.
Pour over slices of bread.

title: frozen coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers.
Cool and split into four. Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar together.
Put this between layers equally, saving 1 cup to mix with Cool Whip.
Use that to frost top and sides.
May be refrozen once thawed.
Keeps for months.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and press into buttered dish.
Spread grated cheese over broccoli.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and cheese.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup with mushrooms

title: pineapple walnut delight
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and dry pudding mix thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip and Pineapple Walnut Delight (can be purchased at deli counters in most supermarkets).
Refrigerate.

title: deluxe brownies with caramel topping
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Cool slightly.
Beat sugar, vanilla and eggs on high speed 5 minutes.
Beat in chocolate mixture on low speed.
Beat in flour just until blended. Spread in 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan that is slightly greased. Bake just until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, 40 to 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with milk.
Stir until smooth.
After brownies finish baking, sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Drizzle with caramel.
Let brownies cool completely before cutting into 2-inch squares. Makes 16 brownies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick, then add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Beat with a spoon to remove any lumps, and pour in cooked crust.
Put meringue on top of pie, or Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.
Very good!

title: suet pudding
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and steam in small coffee can for 3 hours.
When cooled, spread Hard Sauce on.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter in a large saucepan for 10 minutes. Add the stock and bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and potato scallop
directions: Combine mushroom soup, sour cream, water and dill weed in a small bowl.
Blend well.
Alternate layers of potatoes and soup mixture in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper. Brown on both sides in skillet.
Place pork chops on top of potato and soup mixture.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Add sugar and cocoa slowly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line a 12 x 15-inch pan with wax paper.
Pour mixture into pan and bake in a moderate 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
When done, turn out on a towel that has been well sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Place a damp cloth over top. When perfectly cool, spread top with whipped cream and roll like a jelly roll.
Serves 6. Serve with Aunt Mary's Chocolate Sauce.

title: cinnamon cookie ornaments
directions: *If glue is added, cookies are not edible.

title: jamaican casserole
directions: Mash potatoes with butter.
Stir in pineapple, sherry and spices.
Spoon into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: creamed mushrooms
directions: Heat the butter and saute the mushrooms and onions for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in the consomme, salt and pepper.
Cook stirring constantly until the mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir in the cream and heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef and strain grease off.
Cook potatoes and make creamed potatoes with them; add 1/2 stick butter and milk to potatoes after they have been cooked and drained.
Whip potatoes.

title: ham salad
directions: Grate Spam, eggs and carrot.
Add relish and Miracle Whip enough to mix (about 1/3 cup).

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Work in shortening; add egg and milk.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Cover with layer of thinly sliced tart apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and broken walnut (or pecan) meats.
Beat 1 egg with 1/8 cup milk and pour over the top.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: good and healthy meat loaf
directions: Put all the vegetables in a food processor.
Knead the soup mix and vegetables into hamburger meat.
When mixed and kneaded thoroughly, put into a roasting pan.
Please use a roaster rack. Form the meat loaf into shape.
Just roast it where the grease from the meat will drip off the meat loaf and not absorb back into the meat.
Bake at 350°.
Cooking time is 30 minutes; keep checking.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; pour sugar in slow with mixer on high.
Beat until thick and fluffy.
Add vanilla, salt and canned milk.
Pour in freezer can, then finish filling freezer can with regular milk. Freeze.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin, and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the water and the eggs; blend well.
Add remaining water and cook.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; stir in rum.
Chill.
Thoroughly blend whipped topping into chilled mixture.
Spoon into pie crust and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and lime slices.

title: a good potato pudding(adapted from a 17th century recipe)
directions: Mix butter, nutmeg, sugar, salt and pepper into the potatoes; ensure that they are well blended.
Whisk the eggs together with a fork; add them to the mixture.
Spoon it into an ovenproof dish. Bake, uncovered, in a moderate (350°) oven for 35 minutes, or until it is slightly risen and browned on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Stir well first 7 ingredients.
If more moisture is needed, add catsup or tomato juice.
Shape into balls or loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; add mix of catsup, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Pour over meat loaf and return to oven.
Bake until done.

title: crispy baked halibut or chicken
directions: Cut fish into four portions.
Pat dry and brush with cooking oil.
In a shallow baking dish stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, tarragon, paprika and pepper.
Dip fish for chicken into crumb mixture to coat both sides.
Arrange pieces in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle any left over bread crumb mixture on top.
Bake fish, uncovered in a 450° oven 8 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes.
Test with a fork.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Do not overcook.
Arrange broccoli, butt to butt ends, in greased oblong casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put loaf of bread in dish, 2 cups sugar, 3 yolks, can of milk, can of water, bottle of vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon to smell and melted butter.
Now, mix all together.

title: rhubarb-cherry jam
directions: Combine fruits and juices in a heavy saucepan.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add sugar and corn syrup and continue simmering, uncovered, for 15 or 20 minutes or until a nice jam consistency is reached.
Add flavoring.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix well the pineapple chunks, flour, sugar and cheese.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers. Drizzle margarine over the crackers.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni 'n cheese
directions: Toss cooked macaroni in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot.
Stir well. Cover and cook on low 3 to 5 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, flour last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 1 bread pan or 3 coffee cans for 45 minutes.

title: easy caramel apple pie
directions: Combine 10 caramel candies (cut in fourths) and 1/3 cup flour. Add apples, ice cream topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into frozen regular 9-inch Pet-Ritz pie crust and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecan pieces.
Bake at 375° on baking sheet 40 to 45 minutes.
Store at room temperature.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix Russian dressing, apricot preserves and onion soup mix together.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 1 hour or more in refrigerator.
Bake uncovered at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.

title: sticky rolls
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place pecans or walnuts on bottom. Tear 1 loaf of dough on top of nuts.
(Tear pieces about the size of a walnut.)
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread dough in pan.
Rip 2nd loaf into pieces and place in between the pieces of first loaf.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While warm, invert onto a platter.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: 1. Mix ingredients and shape into small meat balls. Roll in flour and brown in hot cooking oil. Drain off.
2. Add 2 c. hot water and the onion soup mix. Simmer for
15 minutes.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place in greased baking dish in order given. Add salt and pepper. Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk; stir in lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top each chicken piece with lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or steamed broccoli.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Stir together until well mixed.
Press into pie pan, reserving 1/2 cup for topping.

title: california salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Combine with coconut and sour cream.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: caramelicks
directions: Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add juice and vinegar. Mash cream cheese with a fork and, while the jello mixture is still warm, add the cheese.
Whip cream until stiff; fold in drained crushed pineapple (use juice with Jell-O).
Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle entire top with chopped pecans.
