Freeze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix real good and bake at 325° in three 1 pound coffee cans until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli and mix with rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's johnny massetti
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Place in baking dish; top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Place all dry ingredients together. Set aside. Cream shortening and sugars together until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins/nuts/spice drops. Drop by teaspoonful onto well-greased cookie sheets.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended with spoon.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake in greased loaf pan (or pans) for 40 minutes in 350 degree oven
(or when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean).

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk and juice thoroughly and pour into crust. Make meringue with egg whites and sugar; spread over pie and lightly brown.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Mix milk, flour and sugar with mixer until smooth.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Pour mixture into margarine and add fruit to the center.
Do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: two-grain date muffins(makes 12 large)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat muffin pans with Pam nonstick spray.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt in a medium bowl.
In a large bowl, stir milk, bran cereal and oats.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes to soften.
Beat in oil and egg to mixture.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened.
Add dates.
Fill prepared muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes, until tops are golden brown and wooden pick in center comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 3 quart casserole dish.
Cut the butter into the dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix nuts into the cake mix.
Sprinkle mixture on top of pumpkin mix.
Bake in 350 oven for 45 minutes - 1 hour. Serve with cool whip or whipped topping.

title: "chill stopping" chili
directions: In large skillet, fry onions and meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for approximately 45 minutes on low heat.

title: easy carrot casserole
directions: Parboil carrots until tender.
Drain well.
Mix carrots with onion seasoning.
Place in alternate layer with grated cheese in a well-buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour melted butter over all. Top with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan; cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until transparent.
Stir in flour; cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings; cook, stirring, until thickened.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and berries, beating until light.
Mix flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg and salt.
Blend flour mixture into berry mixture, just until flour is moistened.
Do not overmix.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Good served with fruit platter and cream cheese.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes in skin; when done, peel and grind. Mix with eggs and butter and salt and pepper to taste. Add enough flour to make dough. Form into a roll about size of broom stick (1 inch). Cut into 1 1/2 inch pieces, drop pieces into boiling salt water. When they float, remove and rinse in cold water; put into casserole and add butter. Put in oven to warm. Can be served with Parmesan cheese. Next day left-overs can be deep fried.

title: great northern delight
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Place in crock-pot.
Cover well with water; add chopped pepper and chopped onion.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on high for 8 hours.

title: holiday rice salad
directions: Cook rice in
chicken
broth
and let cool.
Add in the rest of the ingredients and toss together with the mayonnaise, curry powder and oil/juice from the artichoke hearts.
Enjoy.

title: 6 can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, or until brown on top.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Place apples in pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon over apples.
In mixing bowl combine 1/3 cup sugar, flour and butter; use knife or pastry blender until crumbs are formed. Spread over apples and press down.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Last, add pecans and mix. Make in rolls and freeze.
When you need these, take out and slice, then bake at 350° until set.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix the top 4 ingredients together.
Let get firm.
After it is chilled, mix cream cheese and sour cream together and spread over the top.
Let set for 2 hours before serving.

title: strawberry angel
directions: Make jello with 2 1/2 cups boiling water; stir well.
Add juice from strawberries; stir well.
Add berries and cool until slightly thickened (about 2 hours).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Tear cake in pieces and cover bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with half of cake. Pour half of jello mixture over cake.
Top with rest of cake, then rest of jello mixture.
Chill.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place tuna in bottom of casserole dish.
Bring to a boil the following until thick:
salt, pepper, butter, milk and flour. Stir cheese into the mixture.
Cook until the cheese melts.
Pour the mixture over the tuna, then sprinkle
bread crumbs on top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs and other ingredients, except marshmallows. Put into a greased and floured 9 x 13 baking pan; bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Add marshmallows and put back in oven 5 minutes to melt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; stir until well mixed and peanut butter is melted.
Let cook until mixture forms a soft but firm ball when dropped into cold water.
Take off the stove. Set pan in cold water and stir briskly until it begins to thicken. Pour at once into buttered pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and marshmallow cream until smooth.
Serve with fruit:
whole strawberries, sliced apples, sliced bananas or large seedless grapes.

title: microwave meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Shape into desired size meatballs (they shrink a bit).
Cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Turn and rearrange and cook for 5 more minutes.
Drain. Serve as an appetizer with hot mustard or ketchup or serve on cooked noodles with a can of mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 cup milk and heated as a sauce.

title: cream lime jello salad
directions: Boil ginger ale and pour over Jell-O and cream cheese.
Beat with a fork or mixer.
Congeal some, then add pineapple and nuts. Pour into bowl or casserole dish to congeal.

title: 100-year-old cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening; add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on high for 2 hours, then turn to low for 3 to 10 hours.
Serve warm from crock-pot.

title: steak kebabs
directions: In a shallow glass dish, combine soy sauce, honey, ginger, garlic, lemon peel and red pepper flakes.
Mix well. Add beef; stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Preheat broiler. Remove beef from marinade. Discard marinade.
Using 4 (10-inch) metal skewers, alternately thread beef, tomatoes, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil 2-inches from heat, turning 2 to 3 times, until meat is medium-rare and vegetables are lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: maple cream coffee treat
directions: In
ungreased
x
9-inch
baking pan, combine sugar, chopped
nuts, syrup and 1/4 cup margarine, spreading evenly in pan.
Blend
cream	cheese,
10x sugar, 2 tablespoons margarine and
coconut
until
creamy.
Separate 2 cans Hungry Jack flaky biscuits into
biscuits;
press
or
roll
each to a 4 inch circle.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture onto center of each
biscuit.
Overlap
dough
over filling forming finger shaped rolls.
Place rolls, seam side down in 2 rows of 10-inch pan.
Bake	25 to 30 minutes at 350°, until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes.
Turn onto waxed paper.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: pork chop hot dish
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place thinly sliced potatoes in greased baking dish.
Add sliced onion and top with cheese.
Over this, place carrots,
then pork chops.
Combine soup and milk, pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: hershey's syrup cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended and bake at 350°.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix about 2 minutes on medium speed with electric mixer.
Pour into ready pan.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix dough like biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut saucer size crust.
Put in your favorite fruit.
Fold dough over half and seal edges.
Fry in Crisco.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce.
Layer each vegetable. When ready to serve, add sugar and mayonnaise.
Mix all together.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown pan sausage until crumbly and set aside.
Combine the 2 cheeses.
Pour them into a well-greased baking dish.
Blend the eggs, milk and biscuit mix very well.
Pour this over the cheese. Sprinkle with the sausage.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put ingredients in electric blender and process until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups, same as 14 ounce can.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and roll into a ball.
Cover with cocktail sauce before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble 1/2 cornbread into bottom of a large bowl.
In another bowl, combine peppers, onions, tomatoes, pickles and bacon.
Blend well.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over crumbled cornbread.
Stir mayonnaise and pickle juice in a small bowl.
Spread 1/2 over vegetables. Repeat layers with same as first.
Garnish as desired. Tomatoes are a good choice.
Cover tight and chill for 3 hours or longer.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar

until fluffy. Add milk and vanilla. Stir in flour slowly, then add cherries and nuts. Shape into 3 (7-inch) rolls and roll in coconut flakes. Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly. Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Bake in 375° oven on ungreased cookie sheet approximately 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: carmel corn
directions: Melt butter, stir in brown sugar, Karo and salt.
Bring to boil; stirring constantly, then boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popped corn; mix well.
Place in pans.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool, then store in airtight containers.

title: orange-baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cut oranges in half; clip membranes.
Carefully remove pulp and chop.
Set orange cups and 1/4 cup pulp aside.
Place butter in a glass measure; microwave at High 35 seconds or until melted. Spread pecans in a pie plate.
Microwave at High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Combine sweet potatoes, reserved orange pulp, melted butter, pecans, brown sugar and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture into orange cups.
Place cups on a pie plate; cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: 1015 surprise casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 3/4 cup butter in skillet and saute onions until tender.
Place half the onion mixture in a 1 1/2-quart deep dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs over the onions.
Repeat layers of onions and cheese.
Beat eggs; add cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over onion mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; add 1/2 cup crumbs.
Lightly brown, then sprinkle toasted crumbs over casserole.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Alternate sugar and eggs; beat each time while adding flour.
Pour in tube pan.
Cook 1 hour at 325°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt. Put in casserole. Add bread and raisins.
Pour over enough milk so the bread floats. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: hot chocolate mixture
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. To serve, fill a mug half full with mixture and fill remaining with hot water.

title: taco crescent ring
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain fat.	Add taco seasoning that you have followed directions of on back of package.
Add cheese and place aside.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Place in a circle on cookie sheet.
Place wide side of rolls toward the middle and pointed sides toward the outside.
Place ground chuck on crescent rolls and wrap the pointed ends of rolls around meat mixture forming a ring.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
When baked, remove from oven and place on a large platter.
On the inside of the ring, place lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Dollop sour cream and salsa over all.
Cut into wedges and serve warm.

title: apple crisp(serves 2)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apples in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread sugar-flour mixture over apples.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together all ingredients and pour into greased casserole. Top with 1 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup plain flour, and 1 stick margarine mixed with pastry blender.
Sprinkle topping with chopped pecans to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 9-inch-deep dish pie shell, unbaked.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp with basil leaves
directions: Cut green pepper into 6 pieces.
Slice onion in 1/2-inch wide pieces and cut green onion into 2-inch lengths.
Place oil in wok and heat over medium high flame.
When oil is hot, add all vegetables and chilies.
Stir for 30 seconds.
Turn flame to high. Add shrimp.
Stir once or twice and then add sugar, fish sauce, m.s.g., Golden Mountain Sauce and water.
Stir until shrimp is cooked.
Place on a serving plate.
Serves 2.

title: squash casserole
directions: Spread dressing mix on bottom of casserole dish.
Save 1/4 of mix for topping.
Mix other ingredients and pour into dish.
Top with remaining dressing.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until bubbly.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 16.

title: superb apple pie
directions: Mix together and press into pan.
Do not roll out.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and garlic in olive oil until wilted, but not brown.
Add tomatillos, cover and simmer until soft.
Add cilantro, salt and chilies.
Puree in blender.
This sauce may be prepared and frozen ahead of time.
Grease dish with olive oil. Layer 1/2 the tortillas, chicken, remaining onion, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly. Serve with sour cream and picante.

title: woods landing microwave fish
directions: Soak fillets in water and lemon juice for 15 minutes.
Drain. Dip drained fish in butter.
Place in single layer in microwave dish.
Sprinkle with vegetables.
Microwave on High 7 minutes, rotating dish (covered dish) halfway through the 7 minutes.
Mix soup, sour cream, dash of salt, dash of pepper and dash of paprika and pour over fish and cook, covered, 7 to 10 minutes more.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Place all ingredients in 2-quart casserole greased dish. After 10 minutes baking, take out and mix thoroughly.
Put back in oven 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or as side dish.
Serves 4. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: honey ham chow mein
directions: Cut green pepper in strips, onion in slices and celery in slices.
Heat oil; add onion and ham.
Cook until ham is slightly browned.
Add bouillon, pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Cover tightly; cook slowly for 6 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; add and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve with crisp noodles or rice.

title: mexican casserole(international cuisine)
directions: In skillet, brown meat and pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, chili and water and bring to a boil.
In pan or casserole dish, spoon in enough chili mixture to cover bottom of pan.
Cover mixture with 3 overlapping tortillas.
Cover tortillas with half remaining chili; sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Cover cheese with 3 more tortillas and cover with remaining chili mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cut remaining tortilla into wedges. Remove from oven and add tortilla wedges.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Olive halves may be added if desired.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Re-bake for 10 minutes.

title: heavenly cheese and pasta
directions: Fry beef until cooked through.
Drain off grease. Add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Mix well. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Dip with fresh vegetables.

title: pie crust without the fuss
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Press on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Chill 1 hour.
Fill as desired with fresh fruit or berry combination ice cream, or pudding, or custard.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Beat evaporated milk until stiff adding sugar and jello gradually.
Refrigerate.
Serve in individual dishes.
Sprinkle with crumbs.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off grease. Spread refried beans in a 9 x 14-inch pan. Top with meat that has been mixed with the taco sauce. Cover with cheese.
Can be refrigerated until needed. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use regular or taco flavored Doritos to scoop up meat mixture.

title: beef barley soup(this is a low-fat meal.)
directions: *Can be half pound hamburger or oxtails.

title: onion butter pretzels
directions: Spread pretzel pieces onto greased cookie sheet in a single layer.

Pour melted margarine over top, coating pretzels evenly. Shake soup mix over top thoroughly, covering pretzel pieces. Bake at 275° for approximately 2 hours, stirring several times during baking to coat the pretzels.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Combine pecans and sugar. Add egg whites and mix until mixture is completely damp.
Form into small balls (mixture will be moist).
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press a small hole in the center of each ball with fingertip.
Fill with strawberry preserves.
Top with cherry half, cut side down. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet at once to prevent sticking.
Makes about 36 small cookies.

title: japanese fruit chews
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add nuts, dates, raisins and eggs.
Blend well.
Spread thin on a greased square cake pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into strips while warm and roll in granulated sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies with a twist
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour, sesame seed and baking soda.
In a large mixer bowl, beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds or until softened. Add brown sugar, peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg; beat well on medium speed.
Add flour mixture, beating on low speed until combined.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in wheat germ.
Place 2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet and gently flatten with the bottom of a glass.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown on the bottom.
Remove and cool on a wire rack. Makes about 60 cookies.

title: heavenly hamburgers
directions: Combine the bread cubes, chopped celery, chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste and sage.
To this, add enough warm water to make a rather dry stuffing.
Season the hamburger lightly with the salt, pepper and Accent.
In a greased shallow pan, make a layer with half of the hamburger. Spread the stuffing over top.
Cover with rest of hamburger.
Combine soup and milk with onion soup mix and spread over top. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°. Serves 7.

title: dr. byru's cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add the rest (add bananas last). Blend with spoon (not mixer).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: mrs. bob graham's french silk pie
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven.
Add rest of ingredients and stir every 5 minutes for 20 minutes until crumbly and crisp.
Do not pat down.
Cool and add filling.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well and press into the bottom of a 10x15 pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350 F.

title: stuffed hog maws
directions: Combine potatoes, sausage, onion, carrots and salt.
Stuff in cleaned hog maw.
Close opening with toothpicks.
Put in roasting pan with the water.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Uncover the last 30 minutes.

title: elizabeth's pie(2 pies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter, adding beaten egg yolks. Add vinegar, vanilla, nuts and raisins. Add beaten egg whites. (Do not beat egg whites until stiff.) Pour into uncooked pie crust. Bake in 300° oven until egg whites rise, then turn oven to 250°. Cook until brown or about an hour.

title: hurry-up chili
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for half an hour.

title: tomato soup spice cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift flour, soda,
cinnamon,
cloves and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, with electric
mixer at high speed, cream butter until light. Gradually beat in brown sugar until light.
Add eggs; beat to mix
well. Combine
soup with enough water to measure 2 cups; mix well.
At low speed, add flour mixture in fourths to sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat until combined. Fold
in raisins and nuts.	Pour into prepared pan. Bake for
55 to 60 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan
for	30 minutes before removing.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: carrot-pineapple bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Drain liquid from pineapple into large mixer bowl; reserve pineapple.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla to liquid; beat until mixed.
Add flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes. Stir in reserved pineapple, carrots and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted in the center is withdrawn clean, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 30 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cool on a wire rack until completely cooled.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together.
Pour evenly into two crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cream eggs(easter)
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine very well.
Add coconut and mix thoroughly.
Add sugar and mix by hand until creamed well.
Shape into eggs and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef; mix in taco seasoning, onions and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Blend milk, Bisquick and eggs.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Top with sour cream, tomatoes and avocado.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swedish fruit-soup dessert
directions: Combine mixed fruits, raisins, cinnamon and water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until fruits are tender, about 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling. Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the soy sauce, water, marmalade, jelly and sugars.
Place the chicken in an airtight container. Pour the marinade over the chicken and marinate overnight.
Bake the chicken at 350° for about 1 hour or until chicken is a dark color.

title: chicken a la virginia
directions: Broil chicken.
Place slice of baked or cooked ham on top of waffle.
Place chicken on top of ham.
Syrup or gravy can be poured over the chicken by the guest before eating.
I prefer the syrup.

title: colored macaroni(for art projects)
directions: Place several drops of food coloring or cake icing dye into any size plastic bottle of glue-all.
Allow the bottle of glue to sit for 12 to 24 hours.
The color will continue to spread by molecular action.
Use colored glue to make science, math and art projects tactile.
Use to outline drawings, writing and projects.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together, shortening, sugar and eggs; mix in vanilla and peanut butter. Add flour, soda and salt. Use fork to press in 2-inch circles. Bake at 375° on ungreased pan.

title: kay's butterhorns
directions: Mix milk, margarine and sugar in pan and heat until bubbles appear.
Set aside.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Grease a deep baking dish lightly.
Layer cut chilies on bottom; then layer grated Colby cheese.
Layer green chilies again and another layer of cheese.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Combine other ingredients until dissolved.

title: watermelon ice cream
directions: Get a bowl and line with Saran Wrap.
Divide Cool Whip in half.
Add green food coloring to half and make dark green, as outside of watermelon.
Line the green mixture evenly in bowl. Freeze for 20 minutes.
Put remaining white half of Cool Whip evenly over green.
Freeze for 20 minutes.
Soften sherbet and stir in cut chocolate bits the size of seeds.
Mix well.
Put over top of white layer.
Freeze overnight.
Flip bowl onto dish.
It will come out with green on top as a watermelon would look.
Slice down to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and eggs; add apples and sugar.
Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon together.
Then add to mixture.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Then turn oven down to 300° and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a large skillet, steam onions, celery and green pepper in 1/2 cup water until water evaporates and vegetables are soft.
Add oil and mushrooms; saute until lightly brown.
In a 2-quart greased baking dish, place a layer of zucchini, sauteed vegetables and bread crumbs.
Slice half of oleo over crumbs.
Layer tomatoes and sauce; salt and pepper to taste, then repeat layers.
Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 15 minutes longer, uncovered.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple and fruit jello salad
directions: Put pineapple, apple and banana in when jello is setting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix as given.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside. Blend eggs, sugar and oil until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients. Add zucchini, vanilla and nuts. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Yields two 9 x 5 x 2 loaves.

title: impossible ham pie
directions: Cook in 10-inch pie plate.
Take ham, cheese and onion and sprinkle in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over ham, cheese and onion.
Cook until brown, 35 to 40 minutes, at 400°.
Cool before cutting.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Add spices to taste.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown onion in skillet.
Add ground beef; drain fat.
Add sauce and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Put spaghetti/sauce in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie dish and cook at 300° for 1 hour.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix all but onion rings and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. During the last five minutes, sprinkle with French fried onion rings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add eggs and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: fried purslane
directions: Collect the tender new tips of purslane, about the last two or three-inches from the stems.
Rinse these in water to remove any sand.
Roll them or shake them in flour until thoroughly floured, and then dip in the beaten eggs.
Next cover each purslane stalk with bread crumbs.
This process is easiest to do if you simply line up the three dishes of flour, eggs and bread crumbs and do the breading production-line-style.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt candy bars in microwave.
Let cool slightly.
Stir in Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour in pie crust and chill.
Sliver Hershey bar without almonds to garnish.

title: deer burger casserole
directions: Brown deer burger and cook noodles.
In a large casserole dish, put the deer burger and noodles.
Spread on top of the cream soups.
Put garlic powder in and combine thoroughly and add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in a 350° oven and cook for about 30 minutes.
If desired, one might add cheese on top for the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving. Serve with fish or shellfish.
Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mashed bananas.
Dissolve junket tablets in 1 tablespoon of water.
Add enough milk to fill freezer and freeze.

title: aunt sandy's poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In separate bowl, mix last 3 ingredients.
In 9 x 13-inch bowl, layer 1/2 of second mixture; top with all of first mixture, then top with remaining mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Cool until thickens. Freeze.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and salt.
Drain; add remaining ingredients.
Heat in crock-pot.
Dip chips, crackers, breads, etc.
It's great!

title: no cook meal
directions: Combine carefully while picking out a good restaurant.
Enjoy as often as possible.

title: carrot slaw
directions: Combine carrots, raisins and celery.
Mix sour cream with other ingredients and blend into salad.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pineapple-strawberry milk shake
directions: Slice bananas into 5-cup blender.
Add pineapple juice and strawberries; whir until smooth.
Add ice cream; whir until thick and creamy.
Makes 4 (9-ounce) servings.

title: rice dressing
directions: In a large pot, saute first 4 ingredients in olive oil.
When onion turns clear, add garlic and ground beef.
When beef is cooked, add pork and brown.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, taking time for each ingredient to blend in.
Cook 15 minutes and put into baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: hot breakfast casserole
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Brown the sausage and onion, then drain.
Line a 3-quart buttered casserole with the chiles and tomatoes.
Pour Bisquick mix over top; add meat mixture and top with the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg and mix well.
Pat lightly and evenly in greased 13 x 9 pan.
In separate bowl, beat together the cream cheese, 3 eggs, vanilla and about 7/8 of the box of powdered sugar until creamy.
Pour this mixture on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sift remaining of powdered sugar on top of hot cake; cool and cut into bars.

title: crusty honey whole wheat bread
directions: Heat milk, water, honey and butter to 120°.
Assemble doughmaker.
In large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups all-purpose flour, 1 cup whole wheat flour, yeast, egg, salt and warmed milk mixture.
Mix with doughmaker setting at #12 for 3 minutes. Gradually add remaining whole wheat flour and enough all-purpose flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead with doughmaker until smooth and satiny, about 4 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: nut clusters(candy)
directions: Slowly bring
to boil milk, sugar and butter, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream, vanilla, chocolate and nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well.
Place into pan topping bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves well with anything.

title: kraut 'n brisket
directions: In skillet, brown meat in a small amount of hot oil.
Add onions, water, salt and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add sauerkraut, potato and caraway seed.
Simmer 30 minutes more or until meat is tender.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes; boil until almost done.
(Cover with just enough water to cover potatoes.)
Add onion, salt, pepper and celery to cooking potatoes.
Add whole milk and simmer.

title: autumn fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers and melt butter.
Add eggs, sugar, pineapple, coconut and cracker crumbs.
Put mixture in a greased pan, "tube", if you'd like.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: amy's summer squash(lo-cal, lo-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour until tender.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients (water to molasses).
Slightly cool.
Add yeast.
Beat in eggs, sugar and flour.
Knead.
Mixture may be soft.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide into 2 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 20 slices.

title: dorothy's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding, sugar and milk until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan lightly with oil.
Place a layer of whole crackers on bottom of cake pan and stand pieces around side.
Top with half of pudding mixture and add another layer of whole crackers.
Add remaining pudding mixture and finish with another layer of crackers.
Ice with chocolate frosting; sprinkle with chopped nuts, if you like.

title: diabetic sugarless health cookies(calories: 928 per 18 cookies, 51 per cookie)
directions: Cream the fat until soft.
Chop dates and nuts.
Place the raisins in hot water until softened.
Mix and sift the dry ingredients.
Place the nuts and fruits in this mixture.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until soft ball stirring occasionally, the sugar, milk, oleo and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
First add 2 to 3 tablespoons of peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or platter.

title: pork chop 'n' potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon potato mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Cover. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes more.

title: dusty's buttermilk corn
directions: Cook corn and water for approximately 20 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix cornstarch, milk and flour.
Stir this until smooth.
Thicken the corn with it.
When thick remove from heat and add butter.
Ready to eat.

title: baked pecans
directions: Melt margarine in pan, and put in pecans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Take out, cool, and add 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon white pepper.

title: mommy's easter bonnet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first five ingredients (eggs, sugar, butter, vegetable oil and vinegar).
Beat until smooth and creamy.
In another large bowl, sift together the cake flour and the baking soda.
Begin to alternate this flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk, to the beaten egg mixture, until all the flour and buttermilk have been blended to form the cake mixture.
Add the vanilla and red food coloring, beating until it is the same color throughout the mixture.

title: steak diane
directions: Make sauce by sauteing garlic and onions in 1/4 cup butter. Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce and heat.
Add parsley just before serving.
When ready to serve, heat cast-iron skillet to medium heat and add butter and oil.
Saute tenderloin medallions over medium-high heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until medium-rare.
Serve with sauce on heated plates.
Makes 4 servings.

title: clam dip
directions: Combine the minced clams (with juice), Parmesan, bread crumbs and garlic powder.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; dot with butter.
Top with grated Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: potato onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Pare and cube potatoes. Add to pan with broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in cream.
Heat slowly just until hot.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear washed and drained spinach in bite-sized pieces.
Toss gently with remaining ingredients.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger and sausage; add tomatoes and sauce.
Season to taste.
Simmer.
Prepare dough according to box directions.
Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 13 pan.
Spread dough halfway up sides.
Spread 1 to 1 1/2 cups cheese over dough.
Follow with half of meat mixture.
Spread remaining cheese and another layer of remaining meat mixture. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Crust will look brown.
Cool few minutes before cutting.

title: flank steak pinwheels
directions: Trim all fat off flank steak; cut into 8 crosswise strips. Roll up; secure with small wooden pick.
Place on bottom of slow cooker.
In small bowl, combine all ingredients, except rice or noodles.
Spoon over pinwheels.
Cover; cook on low for about 6 hours, or until tender.
Remove wooden picks.
Serve pinwheels and juices over cooked rice or noodles.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Stir potatoes and salmon together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together with flour and corn meal until thick.
Drop by tablespoons into hot greased frying pan.

title: peggy's skillet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 8-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve as snack cake or coffee cake.

title: mom's fluffy dumplings
directions: If you want chicken and dumplings, cook a chicken in cold water with onion, celery and carrot, added to seasoned water. Reserve hot broth.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, pudding mix, milk and spice in large mixing bowl.

Beat for 1 minute or until well blended. Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Freeze for at least 4 hours or until firm. Let stand in refrigerator 1 hour before serving. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. If desired, add raspberries. Serve immediately.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Mix 1 package of beef with softened cheese and other ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball into second package of cut beef.
Chill 1 hour or more. Ready to eat.

title: granny pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together the flour and salt.
Mix sugar, margarine and Crisco until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each; alternately add dry ingredients and milk and vanilla, beating after each.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until it tests done with toothpick.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Add milk to all the ingredients and cook on medium heat until it comes to a boil. Serve hot. Serve with hot biscuits.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers. Mix crackers, oleo and nuts well. Save 1 cup for topping. Press in 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: luau refresher
directions: Combine all ingredients except carbonated beverage in punch bowl, then add carbonated beverage.
Mix well.
Good with rum or vodka for liquor punch.
Sugar may be added, if desired.
Can make ahead and refrigerate.
Add carbonated beverage before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and let stand in covered dish in refrigerator overnight.
The longer this stands, the better the taste.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand for 1/2 hour. Drop by spoonfuls into deep fryer and cook until brown.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Heat fruit.
Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into casserole.
Do not stir.
Pour hot fruit in middle and do not stir.

title: peloponnese salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and thyme in a jar; shake well.
Cut up lettuce.
Cut tomatoes into wedges and place around edge of bowl over lettuce.
Top lettuce with cucumbers, bell pepper, Feta cheese and olives.
Pour oil and vinegar mixture over lettuce just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Alternate flour and milk, starting and ending with flour.

title: easy sausage and ravioli
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine Prego and ravioli.
Over low heat, heat through; stir often.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grilled three cheese potatoes
directions: Divide the potatoes and onions equally between 2 pieces of heavy-duty foil that have been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Combine Parmesan cheese and 3/4 cup each Cheddar and Mozzarella. Sprinkle cheese over potatoes and onions. Top with bacon, butter, chives, salt and pepper. Bring opposite ends of foil together over filling and fold down several times. Fold unsealed ends toward filling and crimp tightly. Grill, covered, over medium heat for 35 to 40 minutes or potatoes are tender. Remove from grill. Open foil and sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook over low heat until thick and vegetables are done.
Cook large beef roast; shred and add to barbecue sauce.
Serve on buns.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli and drain.
Add all ingredients together and pour
into
greased
or "Pammed" casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea syrup
directions: Steep tea in water for 10 minutes, then stir in sugar.
Use 1 part tea syrup to 3 parts water.

title: peppered steak
directions: Sprinkle round steak with paprika and brown in about 1 tablespoon of oil in large skillet.
Mix bouillon and water and add to steak. Cover and let simmer for about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: green pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together. Cover with boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain. Boil other ingredients together with peppers for about 10 minutes more. Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal. Makes 6 pints.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Combine and mix sugars, shortening, eggs and drained crushed pineapple.
Add the rest; mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crispy apple pie
directions: Peel, quarter and slice apples (thin).	Place in cake pan; add water.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar on top.
Spread dry cake mix evenly; top with chopped pecans.
Slice butter over mixture. Sprinkle cinnamon (to taste).
Cook 45 minutes at 375°.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and half the onion rings.
Spoon half the pea mixture into casserole.
Top with half the cheese. Spoon remaining pea mixture on top. Add remaining cheese and onions on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: uncooked cranberries
directions: Wash berries.
Peel orange.
Put both through food grinder using fine blade.
Put into bowl; add sugar and pineapple and mix well.
Let stand in bottom of refrigerator for a day or two before serving.
The longer it stands, the better.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream the butter with brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts and mix to make a crumb mixture.
(Reserve 2 cups for topping.)
Press remainder in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: string pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper in a large pan over medium-high heat until meat is brown, stirring to separate meat. Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together with 1 cup of the cheese.
Sprinkle remainder on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish, uncovered.

title: shirley's chili
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown meat and onions.
In large pot, add all the ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic or onion.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until thick.
Cook noodles.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, alternate layers of cooked noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and cheese.
Make 2 or 3 layers.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine
flour,
baking
soda, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add
cornmeal and stir.
Add buttermilk, egg whites and margarine. Stir until well blended.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch
pan. Bake
minutes at 450°.
This corn bread is moist and almost like spoon bread!

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Peel potatoes and shell eggs. Dice potatoes into small cubes.
Mash eggs fine with fork.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and Worcestershire sauce with eggs.
Add salt to taste.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Clean and shell shrimp.
Preheat broiler.
Melt butter.
Add olive oil, lemon juice, chopped green onion, basil, oregano, garlic, pepper and salt.

title: fresh strawberry sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add the water, lemon zest and juice.
Stir until cornstarch dissolves.
Add strawberries and heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and boil 2 minutes, stirring. Cool; refrigerate until chilled.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: cauliflower with creme dijon
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Steam until tender; drain. In medium saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour.
Cook stirring for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and half and half.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and whisk in mustard, lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over warm cauliflower in serving dish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite-size balls.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix and shape into log or ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
Chill.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Reserve the juice from the mandarin oranges.
To the juice, add water to make 2 2/3 cups liquid.
Pour this over pudding, Jell-O and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; let cool.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into a mold.

title: toasted cheese sandwich
directions: Toast the bread; put the cheese between toasted bread.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, margarine, eggs and vanilla in blender; cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chef's dressing
directions: Blend
thoroughly
but	gently to preserve tasty little bits of the cheese.
Keep tightly covered and refrigerate.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill for 2 to 4 hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate at least 8 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread 5 minutes in milk.
Add sugar, butter and salt. Pour slowly over beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven until firm.
Set in pan of hot water to bake.
This makes a custard on bottom.

title: cherry dream salad
directions: Mix well pie filling, pineapple, milk and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping and chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: meat and rice roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ground chuck, onions, salt, oregano and egg together.
Add 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce.
On wax paper, press meat mixture into approximately 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Mix rice with the green peppers and 1/4 cup of spaghetti sauce and put in center of meat mix.
Fold meat over rice.
Cut strips approximately 2 1/2 to 3 inches and place in casserole pan or dish. Spoon 1/2 cup of the sauce over strips and bake 25 minutes.
Spoon remaining sauce over loaves and bake 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all together by hand or mixer on low.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and greens pot pie
directions: Saut ham in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium- high heat 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add flour, and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.

Gradually add chicken broth, and cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes or until broth begins to thicken. Bring mixture to a boil, and add seasoning blend and collard greens; return to a boil and cook, stir often, 15 minutes.	Stir in black-eye peas and crushed pepper; spoon hot mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Pour cornbread crust batter evenly over hot filling mixture.
Bake at 425 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes or until cornbread is golden brown and set.

title: country pork chops
directions: Brown
chops in margarine in 12-inch Dutch oven and set aside. Spread
rice in Dutch oven with salt and pepper.
Save 1 tablespoon	of
onion
soup mix and spread the rest over the rice. Drain
mushrooms,	saving the liquid.
Spread mushrooms over the rice and soup mix.	Add enough hot water to mushroom liquid to make 3 cups.
Pour over the rice mix. Put chops over rice
mix. Sprinkle
saved
portion
of
soup mix, apples and onion
over chops.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and cook for 10 minutes more or until liquid is gone.

title: banana chocolate chip bread(yield: 1 loaf)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Use food processor to grind oatmeal very finely.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, oatmeal and remaining dry ingredients.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Form large balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Dough can be frozen and thawed.
Makes approximately 120 large cookies.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix equal parts pineapple juice, cranberry juice, and Sprite in a large punch bowl.

title: foolproof pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add Karo and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell which has been thawed and pierced with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until middle of pie is firm.

title: country steak
directions: Press ground beef paper thin. Make patties about the size of cube steak servings. Lay in baking dish. Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper. Add second layer of meat, flour, salt and pepper. Add third layer of meat and only salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Pour off grease and make gravy. Pour gravy over meat and continue baking for 1/2 hour. Can substitute mushroom soup for homemade gravy.

title: baked chicken
directions: Beat egg with milk and set aside.
Wash and remove skin from chicken; season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dredge in flour, one piece at a time.
Dip in egg mixture and then in cracker crumbs.
Brown in hot oil (about 1 inch in pan) until golden brown.
Peel and slice onion; put in bottom of baking pan. Layer browned chicken on top of onion slices.
Pour the water in the pan and cover pan with foil.
Bake at 375° for about 1/2 hour. Remove foil and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and cold water.
Add the hot water and margarine.
Cook 2 minutes on High in the microwave.
Whisk well, then add 2 beaten egg yolks and cook 2 more minutes.
Put in pie shells and make meringue with the egg whites and a small amount of sugar.
Add to pies.
Brown slightly.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put in large saucepan the sugar, milk, cocoa, salt and Karo syrup.
Bring to boil to soft ball stage.
Add oleo, peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper. Cool.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heavily grease and flour a 9-inch pie plate, bottom and sides.
This helps make the crust.
Put all ingredients into a blender; run just until combined.
Pour into pie plate; sprinkle nutmeg all over the top.
Bake for 40 minutes. Remove from oven; let cool slightly so pie sets.

title: polynesian chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, pineapple or grapes, carrots and almonds.
Blend mayonnaise with sour cream and seasonings.
Pour over chicken and toss lightly.
Chill.
Arrange on lettuce leaves and garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Wash the pork chops; dry them well.
Mix garlic, pepper, oregano and vinegar or lime juice.
Rub into chops and let marinate for 1 to 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a rectangular baking pan large enough to hold the chops.
Beat the eggs with the 2 teaspoons of salt.
Dip the chops into the egg mixture and then again into the bread or cracker crumbs.
Place them in the baking pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: salmon-broccoli bake
directions: Combine rice and apple in oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Place broccoli in single layer over rice.
Spoon salmon over broccoli. Pour prepared hollandaise over salmon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix flavoring into pie filling.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add pie filling and add cake mix.
Stir well with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 20 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: You will need a 2-quart covered pot.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken with bread crumbs.
Heat oil and butter in 12-inch skillet.
Saute breasts until brown. Remove and set aside.
Combine marinara sauce and wine.
Put 1 cup wine sauce mixture in skillet.
Add stocks, rice and olives and stir, scraping bottom of pan.
Pour into lightly oiled 3-quart casserole dish.
Put chicken, skin side down, on rice.
Cover tightly with foil and cook 20 minutes.
Turn chicken, re-cover and cook another 25 minutes.
While chicken bakes, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, eggs marjoram and nutmeg.
Spoon mixture around edges of casserole dish.
Pour remaining wine sauce over chicken. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or more.

title: frankfurter bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Stir in cheese, milk, margarine, flour and salt.
Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine franks with remaining ingredients.
Spoon evenly over noodles.
Bake 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with frozen lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust and refrigerate one hour.
Will keep for 1 week.

title: haber's happening brie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dates with preserves.
Sprinkle flour on flat work surface and roll out puff pastry to size that will completely wrap around Brie wheel.
Place 1/2 of the date/preserve mixture in the center of the pastry in a circle the size of the Brie.
Place the Brie on top and cover with the other half of the mixture.
Carefully wrap the pastry around the Brie, avoiding puncturing the pastry with the dates.
Seal the pastry with drops of cold water.
(Note:
At this point, prepared Brie may be refrigerated for up to two days.
However, return it to room temperature before baking.)

title: honey almond butter
directions: Beat softened butter and honey together.
Stir in nuts.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: simple meal
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato juice and taco mix.
Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box; add to meat mixture. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and bits in double boiler, then add rest and stir well.
Put wax paper (very important) on cookie sheet and drop by teaspoon on sheet and cool.
Store in refrigerator or tight container.
Very easy and very delicious.

title: luxloda finnish salmon and potato casserole
directions: Peeling potatoes is optional.
Quarter potatoes and slice very thin; quarter the slices.
In a 3-quart casserole, layer the ingredients:
potatoes, salmon, onions, seasonings and a few dabs of margarine.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour milk over all.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring spoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: grasshopper ice cream pie
directions: Combine ice cream, lemon juice, creme de menthe and creme de cacao in bowl.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Crush 1 package graham crackers to form a layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, mix milk and pudding according to package directions.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spread pudding over cracker crumbs.
Crush another package of crackers over the pudding.
Place frosting in a small microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High for 30 to 40 seconds, stirring once or twice. Pour over top layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: potato flour sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites to stiff froth and yolks to a velvet cream.
Add sugar to beaten yolks, stir well, then add to stiffly beaten whites.
Add flour and baking powder which has been sifted three times; add flavoring.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower pie
directions: Pour over ingredients in pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots or broccoli with the butter and onions.
Grate cheese and place all ingredients in a slow cooker or crock-pot. Cook on low for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: "bills" baked beans
directions: In a skillet, partially cook the bacon; drain and set aside. In mixing bowl, stir together pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, onion, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Lay the partially cooked bacon atop.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour, until bubbly.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Make small round cookies; roll in crushed cornflakes.
Cut cherries in small pieces and put one in center of cookie to make a wink.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Mix and beat together eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Saute and drain sausage, then add egg mixture.
Add grated cheese and cubed bread slices.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, soup, onion, cheese and sour cream together.
Pour into baking dish and top with remaining butter and corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar and Karo on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and continue for 4 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Add baking soda.
Stir and spread on a greased sheet.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating real good after each addition.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately.
Beat slow until mixed well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Turn mixer on high and whip until real smooth (the secret of this cake is the whipping).
Pour into a 9-inch tube pan that has been well greased.
Put in a cold oven and turn on 300°. Cook for 90 minutes.

title: cheese square puffs
directions: Trim crust from bread and cut into 1-inch squares.
Melt butter and cheese in double boiler.
When smooth and blended, fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin into slices.
Cook meat, onion and mushrooms until brown.
Stir in water, gravy mix, soup and paprika.
Let simmer until well mixed and desired consistency.
Just before serving, add sour cream and mix well.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serve with salad and vegetables.

title: spinach-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables.
Mix sour cream, Worcestershire, salt and lemon juice with vegetables.
Mix in shredded cheese.
Sprinkle some on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make dressing and pour over salad.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Toss together crackers and oil.
Combine other ingredients, then add to crackers and toss until crackers are well coated.

title: cranberry-pear crisp
directions: Mix cranberries and pears in an 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Toss until mixed.
In a small bowl blend flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until topping is golden and fruit is tender.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Top each serving with whipped topping, cream or ice cream.

title: baked beans casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together. Wash kidney beans and drain, then mix all ingredients together. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add cocoa to sugar and mix well.
Stir in 2 cups milk to make smooth mixture and heat in a double boiler.
Beat egg yolks; add flour and mix to a smooth blend with the remaining milk.
Add salt and stir into milk instantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue of egg whites and 8 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly browned.

title: egg chilada
directions: Scramble eggs and season.
Spread salsa on tortillas.
Spoon eggs in center.
Top with chopped onion.
Roll tortilla around eggs and spoon some salsa over top.
Top this with sour cream and garnish with sliced onion and parsley.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Melt together in microwave-proof bowl, shortening and cocoa.
Stir the flour, milk/eggs and shortening/cocoa mixture together.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch greased baking pan.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; set overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Pour in cherry pie filling. Pour pineapple on top. Sprinkle with cake mix. Drizzle melted butter over top. Top with pecans. Bake at 350° until top is slightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: paper bag caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in paper bag (grocery).
Combine sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt in large measuring cup; microwave on full power for 2 minutes until bubbly.
Add baking soda; stir. Pour over popcorn in bag.
Shake to coat corn.
Microwave in bag on full power 1 1/2 minutes; shake again.
Microwave another 1 1/2 minutes on full power.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple chunks together. Add remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: sue's unbelievable easy lasagne
directions: In
skillet,
brown ground beef (scrambled).
Drain off excess fat.
Add	spaghetti sauce.
Heat just until warm.
In 13	x
9 x
2-inch pan, spread about 1 1/2 cups meat mixture; arrange

a layer of uncooked lasagne.	Do not worry about the open spaces at the ends of the pan, the lasagne will expand as it	cooks.	Top lasagne noodles with some meat sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Add another layer of lasagne pressing pieces gently into mixture below.
Repeat other layer additions
using all ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes at 350°, uncover and bake additional 15 to 20 minutes. Allow to stand a few minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine; beat well.
Add sugar, 2 eggs, flour and vanilla; set aside.
Mix brownie mix, 2 tablespoons water and 3 eggs.
Pour 1/2 brownie mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over.
Spoon remaining brownie batter on top.
Pull knife through to swirl.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange zucchini loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.

title: bean noodles
directions: In a large saucepan, cook dry beans until well done and soft. Cook beans in a large amount of water so juice can be used later on to cook noodles (3 quarts or more).
Pour off bean juice in large heavy pan and set aside.

title: pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 10 x 15-inch pan.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix separately butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour and stir in peanut butter morsels.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: egg white cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until soft white peaks form.
Add sugar, gradually beating until peaks are stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper.
Drop mixture in rounded teaspoons.
Bake at 300° about 25 minutes.

title: blueberry cool whip pie
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans on crust.
In one bowl, cream sugar and cream cheese.
In another bowl, thoroughly beat Cool Whip and milk.
Add cream cheese mixture and whipped topping; beat until well mixed.
Pour into crust and add 1/2 can pie filling to middle of pie.
Do not cover all of pie.
It's more attractive if 1-inch or 1 1/2 inches of the cheese filling around the edge is showing.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer. Pour into shells and freeze.
Makes 3 pies.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vinegar together and pour over cabbage and other ingredients.
Add pepper to taste.
Add salt if needed. This makes a large amount; recipe may be halved.

title: chilled asparagus lemonette
directions: Blend all ingredients except asparagus.
Drain asparagus. Arrange asparagus in dish to allow marinade to contact asparagus as much as possible. Cover and marinate for several hours or overnight in refrigerator. Drain before serving.

title: italian chicken vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in large pot; add chicken, water and bouillon. Cook until tender.
Remove chicken to cool.
Add to the pot, stewed tomatoes, broccoli, cauliflower and mixed vegetables; cook until soup comes to a boil.
Add soup pasta, cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Debone and dice cooled chicken breasts; add to soup. Serve.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Mix with other ingredients. Cook in crock-pot for 1 hour.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Whip potatoes and butter with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until light and fluffy.
Place in a buttered casserole and bake at 325°
for 25 minutes, or until hot through.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add diced Ro-Tel tomatoes to melted butter.
Put all other ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° in a covered dish for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: all-american kid chili
directions: Fry ground meat; drain fat.
Add onion and fry a little more. In a larger pot, put ground beef, baked beans, ketchup, brown sugar and mustard.
Let cook together for 20 minutes, until beans soften somewhat and sauce thickens.

title: cardamom bread(kardemonmme brod)
directions: Scald milk over low heat; add cardamom.
Remove from heat; pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add butter and stir until melted. Stir in sugar and salt.
Beat in egg.
Blend yeast with 2 cups flour in small bowl.
Add milk mixture and beat well (about 3 minutes).
Gradually add enough additional flour to make a firm, but soft dough.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes on a lightly floured surface.
Round up in greased bowl and let rise in warm place, 45 to 75 minutes.
Divide dough and shape into two loaves.

title: baked beans medley
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
In a large skillet, cook onion and bacon until onion is tender and bacon crisp.
Drain off fat.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix beans, tomato sauce, water, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Add onion and bacon mixture; stir until blended.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and stir.
Bake, uncovered, about 10 minutes or more until desired consistency.
Stir in Equal.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugars.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Prepare a sauce from margarine, poppy seed, onion flakes, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut rolls open; spread with sauce.
Place slice of ham and slice of cheese on each roll.
Wrap tightly with foil, refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: jeweled fruit cake
directions: *Or any combination of dried fruits (bananas, pears, peaches).

title: fried chicken
directions: Skin chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge it with flour.
A quick and efficient way to flour is to place chicken with flour in a paper bag and shake vigorously.
Place oil in frying pan (2 inches of oil; needs to cover chicken).
Use an iron skillet.
Allow oil to become very hot before putting chicken in skillet.
Reduce heat slightly after placing chicken in skillet. Continue to cook about 20 to 25 minutes on each side.
Serve.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to boil. Add cream cheese and stir until melted. Add gelatin to water and let stand 5 minutes. Add gelatin to hot soup and cool. Add celery, onion, shrimp and mayonnaise. Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and red food color until well mixed.
Add salt, banana, sugar, pineapple and lemon juice and stir.
Fold in chopped nuts and sweet cherries.
Spoon into paper muffin cups which have been place in 3-inch muffin pans.
Freeze.
Remove from pans and place into plastic bags.
Keep frozen until ready to use. About 30 minutes before serving, thaw slightly at room temperature.
Will keep for 6 to 8 weeks in the freezer.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: honey bun cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix cake mix with 1/2 cup sugar; beat in the oil and eggs.
Add the sour cream and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together and swirl with knife into cake batter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: e z cheesez appetizer
directions: Mix together all Cheddar cheese, green onions, almonds, garlic powder and mayonnaise.
Put on Ritz or Club crackers.
It is good to let sit in the refrigerator for a short period of time to let flavors mix.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; mix well.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into 9-inch square dish.
Chill.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into 24 tarts.
Press in miniature cupcake pans.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes for 10 to 15 minutes or bake in oven at 450° for 45 minutes.
Then cut potatoes in half and scoop out the potato into a bowl.
Now add butter, cheese, sour cream, milk, salt, pepper and fried bacon (broken up).
Mix together and put back into potato shells.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Boil noodles (do not cook fully).
Drain and sprinkle with parsley and garlic powder.
Saute onion, celery, garlic and bell pepper in butter.
Add shrimp; cook for 2 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, Cheez Whiz and half and half.
Pour over noodles; bake at 350°, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes in the oven.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg, milk and softened shortening.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Bake in heated greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco salad - mexican
directions: While preparing all the salad mixings, brown the ground beef. Drain off the grease and add the kidney beans.
Simmer 10 minutes, then mix with the cold salad.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in 1 1/2-quart bowl the flour, sugar and salt; add syrup, eggs, evaporated milk and pecans.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until firm.
Cool before serving.

title: *blueberry fluff
directions: In a large bowl, beat Cool Whip and condensed milk until smooth.
Mix in all remaining ingredients by hand.
Refrigerate in serving bowl for at least 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamed chipped beef on toast
directions: Shred beef into small pieces.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Sprinkle in flour, stirring constantly until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and cook 5 to 8 minutes more, until sauce is thick.
Add beef, then pepper and salt to taste.
Add parsley and remove from heat.
Serve on toast or waffles.
Serves 4.

title: ruby cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add next 3.
Batter will be thick.
Add fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased baking pan. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, sherry and soup.
Pour into baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in saucepan.
Cook and stir it over medium heat until it gets bubbles around the edge.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the soda until foamy.
Bake caramel corn 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes in two 13 x 9-inch pans.
Store in tightly covered container or wrap in transparent wrap.

title: venison sausage
directions: Be sure the fat, ligaments and tissues are all trimmed from the venison.
Use the amount of seasonings listed for 10 pounds of the meat mixture.
Mix all thoroughly.
Make into patties for frying or into rolls for use.
This freezes nicely.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch. Measure 3/4 cup evaporated milk and set aside.
Stir the remaining evaporated milk, the chocolate and 1 tablespoon margarine or butter into sugar mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Gradually stir about 1 cup of hot mixture into egg yolks; return mixture to saucepan and bring to gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla. Turn hot filling into baked pie crust.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Deep fry* at 400° (high) for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy; drain.

title: orange ring mold
directions: Mix in order given and pour in ring mold.
Chill until set.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, vanilla and margarine.
Beat in sugar and eggs one at a time.
Add salt and flour; put in cookie sheet pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake; you want these chewy.

title: cranberry-orange cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and lemon juice.
Stir in cranberries and rind.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and a few dashes of garlic powder. Spread into the bottom of a pie plate. Spread pizza quick sauce over the cream cheese mixture.
Add green pepper, pepperoni and onion.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and bake for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and butterscotch chips on top of batter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 3/4 cup.
Put rest in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour melted butter over cookies and refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: potato and ham soup
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Simmer until vegetables are tender. Add milk, butter and diced ham. Heat just to boiling. Serve at once. Makes about 6 cups.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix together cake mix*, melted butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in bowl.
Spread half of mixture (1 1/2 cups) evenly in the prepared pan.
Bake for 6 minutes.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, pudding mix, eggs, 3/4 cup peach Schnapps, 1/2 cup orange juice and the orange extract together.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the eggs and sugars.
Add the corn oil, salt, flour, soda, apple pie spice and vanilla.
Fold in the apples and nuts.
Mix ingredients in the order given.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes.
Melt butter in small pan.
Arrange potatoes, skin side down, on a cookie sheet.
Brush with butter and bake for 25 minutes in 450° oven.

title: amish bread starter
directions: Divide into 4 parts (4 cups).
Bake as many as you want, give some away or it can be put in your freezer.

title: candy mints
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, water, oil flavoring and coloring thoroughly.
(I use my hands.)
Roll in small balls the size of a marble and dip in superfine granulated sugar.
Dip your mold in the granulated sugar and press the ball down on your mold.
Unmold at once on waxed paper.
When candies have hardened, approximately 24 hours, you may remove and store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 80 mints or candies.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend these together and dip with apple slices.

title: frozen slush punch
