directions: Mix Jell-O (flavor of Jell-O for color of punch) with boiling water in large container.
Cool.
Bring 4 cups of water and 4 cups of sugar to a boil in a saucepan.
Cool and add to Jell-O mixture. Pour in pineapple juice and lemon juice and stir well.
Pour into 2 gallon plastic milk containers and freeze.
Thaw for 4 hours. Cut top off plastic milk containers and pour into large punch bowl.
Slush and add 2 bottles of ginger ale to each gallon of punch.

title: scallopine with lemon
directions: Soak scallops in beaten egg for 1 hour.
Pat well with some flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown slowly on both sides in the butter.
Add wine.
Let evaporate.
Then pour on the broth and lemon juice.

title: fast peach cobbler
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Pour into greased pan. Pour fruit on top and swirl gently.
Bake at 350° until fruit sinks to bottom and crust is lightly browned.
Serve as is or with ice cream, cream or Cool Whip.

title: ham and egg salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
Combine shells, ham, cheese, eggs and onion.
Blend together mayonnaise, mustard, salt, sugar and pepper.
Toss dressing with salad and chill.

title: cherry whip
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip and pineapple together.
Add remaining ingredients; whip with spoon.
Chill until it sets.

title: basic light cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt
butter in saucepan;
brown meat.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Stir
in
remaining
ingredients,
except flour and milk. Cook over low heat until vegetables are tender, about 20 to 25 minutes. Combine flour
with
cup
milk.
Stir into soup mixture.
Boil.
Add remaining milk and heat, stirring frequently.
Do not boil after adding remaining milk.
This makes quite a large amount.
(Green pepper can be substituted for celery.) This is also a good recipe to can as vegetable soup, omitting flour and milk until opening.

title: chicken dish
directions: Saute onion in butter on low heat.
Salt and pepper chicken and cook, covered, on low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken to platter.
Add cream, curry, brandy or Madeira in existing juices in pan.
Stir over low heat, but do not boil or cream will curdle.
Return chicken to pan and spoon sauce over it. Can be served with rice and salad.

title: pasta with shrimp and scallops
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil and butter until tender. Add the mushrooms; season with salt and pepper and saute.
Add the white wine.
Boil and reduce by half.
Add the tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the shrimp and scallops and simmer for 5 minutes.
Boil spaghetti and drain; toss it with sauce.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender.
Peel; cut in thin slices into bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; reserve 1/3 cup bacon fat.
Brown onions in reserved bacon fat in skillet.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper; add to onions.
Stir in water and vinegar gradually; cook, stirring,
until mixture boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over potatoes; add crumbled bacon.
Mix lightly.
Garnish with eggs.
Serve warm.
May be rewarmed over hot water. Yields 6 servings.

title: old time egg pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into shell and bake at 350° until firm.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cheesy hash brown potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients (except cornflakes); top with crushed flakes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar. Place in 9
x
13-inch
baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, boil sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in the margarine until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour onto a small wax paper lined cookie sheet, cool and cut into bars or drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small pieces, not crumbs.
Put half in bottom of buttered deep baking dish.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to applesauce and spread over bread in dish, then cover with remaining bread.
Dot with butter.
Mix milk, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla and pour over bread.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until pudding is puffed and set.

title: grannie's peanut butter caramel cake
directions: Blend Crisco until creamy.
Add sugar.
When well mixed, begin adding eggs, one at a time, mix well.
Blend together flour, baking powder; set aside.
Add to egg mixture 1 cup flour mix at a time, alternating with buttermilk until all has been added.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix only until combined.
Do not over beat. Line 5 greased and floured pans with wax paper.
Put 8 - 9 tablespoons of batter in each pan.
(Very tiny layers are what makes this cake special.)
Bake at 400 degrees until done.
WATCH CAREFULLY, takes only 6 - 10 minutes.

title: bubble buns
directions: Combine the first three ingredients.
Separate biscuits; cut each into four parts.
Roll into balls.
Coat each ball generously with mayonnaise, then roll in sugar mixture.
Place 4 in each muffin cup with paper liner.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes at 400° or until browned.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows to jello.
Let set until firm.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix the wet ingredients into the combined dry ingredients until moistened.
Fold in the blueberries.
Pour into paper-lined or greased muffin tins and bake at 400° until golden brown. Yields 8 muffins.

title: graham cracker cake(good to make with kids.)
directions: Layer bottom of square baking dish with graham crackers. Prepare puddings according to directions on box.
Spread 1/2 of the chocolate pudding on top of the graham crackers.
Next, add another layer of graham crackers, then 1/2 of the vanilla pudding.
Repeat layering.
You should have two alternating layers of chocolate and vanilla with graham crackers in between each layer.
Refrigerate and chill for 1 hour.

title: quick rolls
directions: Put dry yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/3 cup of lukewarm water.
Stir and let set 3 or 4 minutes.
Then put melted shortening, 4 tablespoons sugar and salt into large mixing bowl. Add cold milk to this, then the yeast mixture and enough flour to make stiff dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Chop bacon into small cubes. Fry until almost crisp in a double broiler. Add chopped onion to bacon and cook until the onions become almost transparent. Add vinegar, water, and sugar to the onion and bacon. Salt and pepper to taste (add crushed peppers if desired). Simmer 20 minutes. Drain and rinse green beans. Add to bacon mixture and simmer for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with hands.
Roll into marble size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° 25-30 minutes until brown.
Turn each one over at least once during cooking.
Makes approximately 75.

title: chicken salad
directions: This is good served in pita pockets.

title: premium chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl. Set aside. Beat butter and sugars in large bowl with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chunks and nuts. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or just until golden brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Put sugar, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, Mazola oil and softened oleo into large bowl.
Beat well with mixer until light and fluffy, then add dry ingredients, adding the flour last.
Chill and roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
May mix red and green sugar with white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: green peas casserole
directions: Mix peas, mushroom soup and water chestnuts and place in a buttered baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven until bubbly.
Remove from oven, add onion rings, return to oven and bake about 5 to 10 minutes until onion rings brown.
Serves 8.

title: mom's deep dish pizza dough
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest for about 5 minutes before pressing dough evenly on the bottom and halfway up the
sides
of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with toppings. Bake for 20 minutes at 450°.

title: venison stew
directions: Roll venison in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown in 1/2 cup oil.
Place browned meat and remaining ingredients in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Blend ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Put boiled and drained sweet potato in mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Mixture will be rather thin. Pour into an oiled pie plate and bake at about 375° for around 30 to 40 minutes.
(I melt the margarine in the pie plate.)
The pie will rise while cooking and then fall when cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together well.
Put into pie shells and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add the beaten egg yolks. Sift together the dry ingredients. Add water to the mashed bananas and mix well. Add the dry ingredients alternately with the banana mixture to the first mixture. Add nuts. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Test with toothpick.

title: peach cream cobbler
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, butter and coconut.
Blend until crumbly.
Press into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake for approximately 10 minutes at 350° until lightly browned. Remove from oven and cool.

title: mini fruitcake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs, honey and vanilla until fluffy.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Gradually blend half the flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Stir the nuts and fruit in remaining flour and blend with rest of the dough.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of dough onto greased cookie sheet, spacing 2 inches apart.
Bake one sheet at a time for 15 to 20 minutes or until centers of cookies spring back when lightly touched.
Cool on racks.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: cooked apples
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields about 5 1/2 cups.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook frozen spinach as directed and set aside.
Brown beef and sausage and drain.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, Worcestershire sauce and stir in spinach.
Cook lasagne noodles.

title: stir-fried chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Stir-fry chicken, onion and garlic until onion is transparent.
Add carrots, asparagus, cauliflower and mushrooms. Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes until vegetables are tender. Serve over spaghetti and top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.
One-thousand calorie recipe.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour fluted tube pan. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large mixing bowl beat eggs and sugar.
Combine oil and orange juice.
Add to flour mixture alternately with sugar mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.

title: e. z. duz-it cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar and water. Pour mixture over the butter.
Dump 1 can of pie filling over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: beef and eggplant casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Combine with the onion, garlic, dill and pepper. Slice the eggplant or squash into long slices, about 1/8-inch thick.
In a casserole 8 x 8 x 2-inch, arrange one layer vegetables, then a layer of meat.
Repeat this one more time, ending with a layer of vegetables.
Pour yogurt on top of this mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes until casserole starts to bubble.

title: mexican family dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain off fat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add beans, seasonings, soup, tamales and cheese.
Simmer on top of stove for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Combine pineapple, banana, milk and sherbet in blender; process until smooth.
Makes 3 cups.

title: magic cookie bars(7 layer bars; dieters downfall)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if using glass).
In a 13 by 9 in. baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; mix together and press into pan.
Sprinkle over crumb mixture the chips, coconut and nuts; one ingredient at a time. Pour milk evenly over top.
Bake for 25-30 min. or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour or until done. Remove from oven.
Cut in half lengthwise.

Scoop out potatoes (careful not to break shell) in saucepan. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Beat until fluffy. Add more sour or heavy cream and butter or margarine if necessary. Fill potato shells. Sprinkle with cheese of your choice.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: wayne's hot fudge sauce
directions: Place milk and sugar in large pot and bring to a rolling boil. Boil for one minute.
Add chocolate squares; when melted, remove from heat and beat until smooth with mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat again with mixer.
Serve warm.
Can be stored in refrigerator and reheated in the microwave.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Keep your heat down to avoid burning. Place beans, ham and onions in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix tomatoes and mustard separately; pour over ingredients in casserole.
Top with brown sugar.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Drop by teaspoon into hot Wesson oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: jello pie
directions: Pour milk in bowl, place in freezer until ice crystals form. Mix sugar, Jell-O, eggs and pineapple.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
Beat milk until fluffy and fold in hot mixture.
Pour in 2 wafer crusts.

title: meat loaf or meat balls
directions: Mix milk and egg.
Break bread into small pieces and add to milk mixture.
Add salt and other ingredients.
Mix well and shape into loaf or meat balls.

title: fruit flavored gelatin
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on 1/4 cup cold juice.
Heat one cup fruit juice.
Add to gelatin to dissolve.
Add remaining juice.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Use cookie cutter to make shape.

title: green pea salad
directions: Cook peas according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Toss with red pepper, water chestnuts, scallions, yogurt, salt, pepper and herbs.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini and cook until done.
Saute green pepper, garlic, onion, mushrooms and celery in butter.
Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Drain zucchini in strainer.
While in strainer, lightly mash and then let drain again to eliminate excess liquid. Pour into casserole.
Add bacon crumbs, sauteed vegetables, lightly beaten egg and bread crumbs.
Blend.
(The consistency should be rather mushy.)
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut lard into flour.
Combine remaining ingredients by beating with a fork.
Add flour and stir with fork.
Work with hands into 4 balls.
Roll out.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: cranberry orange nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut butter into dry ingredients; add juice and egg.
Mix well.
Add nuts and cranberries.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans (one 9 x 5 x 3-inch or three 10 ounce loaf pans). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add the 2 cans of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over apples to taste.
Sprinkle the sugar over the apples.
Sprinkle cake mix dry over the mixture and then add the nuts.
Chip butter in small pieces over top.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes so cake mix absorbs some of the apple juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: *Can use 3 tablespoons flour and 3 tablespoons oat bran; this absorbs the moisture from the pumpkin.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash lettuce and layer in bottom of casserole dish. Continue layers in order above, ending with onions. Mix mayo and sugar until well blended. Spread over top of layers. Top with cheese. Place in the refrigerator overnight.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with strips of uncooked bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and butter until creamy.
Add other ingredients and mold into a ball.
Chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch tin.
Spread pie filling next.
Sprinkle white cake mix over.
Slice oleo over cake mix. Chop nuts and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn bread pot pie
directions: Mix meat, vegetables, cheese, 1 cup milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into greased baking dish or shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until bubbly at edges.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onions, green peppers and beef.
Brown for about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, rice, 1 teaspoon chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well and simmer, covered.
Toward end of cooking, add additional chili powder.
Add water if too dry; should be moist, not soupy.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 6 cups water with chopped celery stalk, onions, bay leaf and peppercorns for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken and allow to cool. When cool, cut into small cubes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in boiling, salted water with a pinch of sugar until really done and tender.
Drain in colander.
Put back in pot and add a lot of butter.
Mash fine with potato masher. Stir in sour cream and cheese.
Turn into a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple flop cake
directions: Mix by hand flour, sugar, crushed pineapple and soda.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fried oysters
directions: Wash oysters by placing them in a colander and running water through them, moving them gently with your hands.
This eliminates sand and grit.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Mix jello with boiling water. Stir in orange juice. Cool.
Add oranges and pineapple (drained).
Pour into dish. Chill until set. Whip the cream. Beat pudding until slightly set. Fold cream into pudding and spread on set jello.
May be used as a salad or dessert.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add salt to cukes and let stand for 3 hours.
Squeeze out excess water.
Grind next 3 ingredients.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard and turmeric.
Mix all ingredients well and cook for ten minutes.
Seal in pint jars.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: fluffy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare topping mix with 1 cup of the milk as directed on package.
Measure 2 cups of prepared topping and put aside.
Add 1 cup milk and chocolate and mix to remaining whipped topping. Blend, then beat on high 2 minutes.
Spoon over crumbs.
Clean bowl and beaters.
Mix the remaining topping, milk and vanilla pudding and peanut butter.
Blend, then beat on high 2 minutes. Spoon over chocolate filling.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Bring to boil in saucepan.
Boil 2 full minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Whisk together sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, whisking constantly. Boil, stirring often, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in butter and vanilla.

title: meagan's apple macaroon swirly buns
directions: In a small bowl, mix together the teaspoon sugar with the warm water and yeast.
stir and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the brown sugar, apple juice, egg, cinnamon, melted butter, yeast mixture and 2 cups of the flour.
Mix well, using a wooden spoon.
Work in the remaining flour, as needed, to make a moderately firm dough. Turn the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth.
Shape into a ball and place in a large, oiled bowl.
Turn the dough over so that all surfaces will be lightly oiled.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour. While dough is rising, prepare the coating.

When the dough has doubled in size, punch it down. Pinch off pieces about the size of a golf ball. Roll pieces between palms of hands until you get ropes about 8 or 9 inches long. Dip the ropes into the melted butter, then coat in the macaroon mixture.
Swirl into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375 degrees for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove from tins and place buns on rack to cool slightly.
Drizzle with glaze.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine.
Chill thoroughly.
(Three cups of chicken equals 3 large breasts, a skimpy 3 pounds.)

title: szechwan shredded chicken
directions: Fry for 10 seconds.
Add cornstarch and stir well.
Remove and serve.

title: tuna shoestring salad
directions: Drain and flake tuna in bowl. Stir in celery, carrot and Miracle Whip. Just before serving, add potato sticks. Serve on lettuce leaf or shredded lettuce, if desired.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Chill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: green bean medley
directions: Brown meat until done.
Drain.
Grease casserole dish.
Layer bottom of dish with meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Next, top meat with green beans, mushroom soup, onion rings and Tater Tots.
Bake in 350° oven until done, hot and bubbly, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 or 6 servings.

title: cheese dip for chips
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt
cheese and milk in a microwave dish, stirring often.
When it's all melted, stir in the drained sausage.
It's ready for dipping.

title: raisin-oat squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix melted butter or margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift all-purpose flour with baking powder and salt.
Blend into the sugar mixture.
Add rolled oats, orange juice, seedless raisins and chopped nuts (optional).
Mix ingredients thoroughly and spread into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Boil six good sized potatoes with their jackets on.
Take them out with a skimmer.
Drain and squeeze with a towel to ensure being dry.
Remove skin and mash them perfectly free from lumps. Add a tablespoon of butter, one egg and a pint of sweet milk. When cool, beat in half cup yeast.
Put in just enough flour to make a stiff dough.
When the mixture rises, make into small cakes.
Let them rise the same as biscuits.
Bake to a delicate brown.
This dough is
very fine dropped into meat soups or pot pies.

title: holiday delight cake
directions: Melt butter and add flour and nuts.
Press this into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar and spread over crust.
Chill.
Mix milk and pudding and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Chill for several hours.

title: oniony oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large Ziploc bag, place all ingredients and shake until potatoes are coated.
Pour in a shallow baking pan.
Bake approximately 40 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes until potatoes are tender and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange summer cooler
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender for 30 to 60 seconds.
Pour into tall glasses.
Yield:
4 servings (2 3/4 cups).
Serving size: 2/3 cup.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onions and carrots as directed on package.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Stir in cheese. Top with potatoes.
Bake uncovered until bubbly, about 10 minutes.

title: never fail custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Bring milk to a boil.
Add milk to egg mixture slowly, beating as you mix.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: southern belle pecan cookies
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and stir in sugar.
Remove from heat, mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together until blended.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: quick chocolate almond candy
directions: Line 10 x 15 pan with foil.
Spray generously with Pam. Cover pan with crackers.
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over top of crackers.
Put in the oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture. Top with sliced almonds.
Cut while warm.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and sugar together. Mix oil, buttermilk, eggs, vinegar, vanilla and food coloring together and pour into flour mixture. Cook at 350° for around 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: *One can chicken stock can be substituted for part of tomato juice.

title: five cup salad
directions: Add cherries and nuts, if desired.
Mix and chill.
Better if chilled overnight.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Chop onions and bell peppers; toast 1/2 bag of bread and then mix (tearing the toasted bread into small pieces) with onions and peppers (kneading).
Pull off the amount of size of meatballs until all used.
Then deep fry for 5 minutes on medium-high; then mix the brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce together.
Spread on meatballs.
Let set for 10 minutes and serve.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Spread into pan.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 25 minutes.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: hidden valley salad
directions: Unfold crescent rolls and layer on bottom of long Pyrex dish. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.
Let cool.

title: ham and egg puff
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Line the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 8 slices bread.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese over bread; cover with remaining 8 slices bread.
Beat eggs with salt, mustard and milk.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Before baking, sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued stuffed fish
directions: Wash fish quickly in cold water and pat dry.
Rub cavity with salt and pepper.
Stuff with Garden Vegetable Stuffing.
Close opening with skewers and lace with string.
Brush fish with salad oil.
Place fish in wire basket 4 to 6-inches from medium coals. Cook 45 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork, turning 3 times and basting with mixture of butter and lemon juice.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Peel and seed the cucumbers.
Chop finely and cover with salted ice water for 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix with cream cheese (at room temperature).
Add seasonings.
Seed and drain the tomatoes; do not peel.
Take a thin slice from the bottom so tomatoes will stand upright.
Stuff with the mixture.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix batter with a spoon until combined.
Put into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Place into a 350° preheated oven. Cook until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package.
Beat eggs and mix in spinach and other ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Add bread crumbs on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast biscuit bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk and yeast to dry mixture.
Mix well. Let stand a few hours or overnight if you like.
Turn out on board.
Roll to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut.
Dip in butter.
Bake at 400°.

title: island punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Blend the flour and milk in a saucepan.
Mix well; cook over medium
heat
until
smooth and thick.
Cool completely. Beat the oleo or margarine, shortening and sugar with electric mixer
at high speed for 10 minutes.	Add flour mixture; beat until
well blended.
Add
the vanilla;
mix well.
Spread on cake.

title: coconut lemon squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Rub in margarine and add milk.
Put half of mixture in square pan and pour lemon filling over.
Then put remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ugly dip
directions: Mix well and let set in refrigerator for at least 8 hours. Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 55 minutes or until done.
Grease bottom of pan only.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Break eggs in a dish with melted butter.
Mix sugar and flour together, then
mix
these	4 ingredients together.
Add vanilla and buttermilk; mix
well.	Pour
into
a 9-inch crust and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: barb-q-roast
directions: Put roast in foil-lined pan.
Sprinkle with tenderizer.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Start putting sauce on roast. Bake another 45 minutes.
Turn over and put more sauce on roast. Bake until done.
Take out of juice and slice.
Put slices back into pan with juice and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn
directions: Melt cream cheese, milk and garlic salt in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in corn and jalapenos.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in greased dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese or paprika, if desired.

title: sunset cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Blend in flour.
Form into 4 rolls of about 1 1/2 to 2-inches in diameter and 10 to 12-inches long.
Roll each log in colored sugar.
Place on tray; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin, about 1/4-inch, and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Yield:
8 dozen cookies.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil; boil for one minute.
Remove
from
heat.
Stir
in oats and peanut butter; stir well.
Drop
by
teaspoons
on
waxed paper. Add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with seasoned croutons.
Return to oven 5 to 10 minutes until croutons are browned.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup. Pour over chicken.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.

title: pasta and vegetable salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain and cool.

title: rice-apple crisp
directions: Combine rice, apples, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and salt in buttered shallow baking dish.
Mix flour and remaining sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in nutmeats. Sprinkle over rice and apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook until thick the egg yolks, juice, sugar and cornstarch. Add macaroni, oranges and pineapple; let stand overnight.
The next morning add small marshmallows, maraschino cherries and nuts. Also add a large container Cool Whip.

title: shrimp lajour
directions: Cut jumbo shrimp down the middle, long way.
Put as much horseradish in slit to liking.
Cut a strip of bacon in half and wrap it around the shrimp.
Bake at 375° until bacon is crisp, about 1/2 hour.

title: blackened shrimp stroganoff
directions: Peel shrimp; save shells.
Place shells in 1 cup water, bring to boil, reduce heat, simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Strain and discard shells.
Coat shrimp with oil and blackening, set aside. Cook mushroom and onion in butter until tender.
Cook shrimp until pink, approximately 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Boil vermouth until reduced to 1/4 cup (2 to 3 minutes).
Stir together sour cream and cornstarch, stir in shrimp broth, add to skillet. Cook until thick and bubbly.
Cook 1 minute more.
Add shrimp, red peppers, mushrooms and capers.
Heat through.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion rings and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Put onion rings on top.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all except coconut.
Drop by teaspoon in coconut.
Roll and form into balls.
Lightly grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: glenda's salad
directions: Mix well.
Pour over salad and toss with 1/2 cup sliced almonds.

title: vegetable soup(diet)
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 20 minutes longer.

title: fish house punch
directions: Combine
water
and
pineapple
juice with brown sugar. Heat to make a syrup and pour over rinds and juice of lemons. Cool; add
rum
and
brandy
and dash well with peach brandy. Serve in bowl with crushed ice.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: party fruit freeze
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cheese; add other ingredients. Freeze in 9 x 5 x 3 pan.

title: spanish cocoa cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda together 3 times. Cream the shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, blending after each addition.
Pour into greased pan and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes one 8 x 8-inch cake.

title: picante dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with chips and raw chilled vegetables.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Slice off top of tomatoes.
Sprinkle with basil.
Place a small slice of Feta cheese on top and sprinkle with desired amount of cayenne pepper.
Bake in a 400° oven just until Feta is browned, 7 to 10 minutes.

title: beef teriyaki
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in oil.
Add ginger, pepper strips, beef broth and soy sauce.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: In saucepan, add raisins and water.
Cook until water is gone; set aside.
Beat together the oil and sugar; add beaten eggs, then vanilla.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, vanilla and raisins. Add to mixture; stir well.
Mixture will be fairly stiff.
You may have to work in by hand.
Form into balls.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: chinese chop suey
directions: Slice onions (long way).
Cut celery into 1-inch pieces.
Melt margarine; cook celery 5 to 10 minutes.
Add onions; cook 5 minutes more.
Add drained bean sprouts (drained well).
Add 1 1/3 cups of broth and cover; cook for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, with leftover chicken broth (2/3 cup).
Add the cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar.
Add to bean sprout mixture and cook 10 minutes more, along with diced chicken.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, egg, oleo and powdered sugar, then set aside.
Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture in 8-inch flower pot. Decorate with seasonal flower and watch to see if it gets eaten!

title: crab muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on muffin halves; cut into quarters and broil until brown and bubbly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large plastic bowl, mix first 4 ingredients. Add half of the dry ingredients which have already been sifted together.
Mix well. Add remaining half.
Fold in nuts, cherries and raisins. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and fill 2/3 full.
Bake 1
hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: butter bean salad(lima bean)
directions: Boil butter beans until just done, not soft.
Drain, add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled (overnight is best). Drain the part to be eaten.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Braise onion, green pepper and celery. Add ground beef. Drain after braising. Mix ketchup with ground beef mixture. The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Mix milk and chicken soup together; set aside.
Layer cubed chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place stuffing on top of chicken.
Top with soup mixture.
Add salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Cover; place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: hawaiian tsukemono
directions: Wash
and
slice daikon and pack it in a gallon jar, at least 3/4
full.	Mix salt, sugar, vinegar and turmeric well, and
pour the
mixture
over	the
daikon.
Let it sit for 12 hours.	Mix well
again
and let it sit for another 12 hours. If the
seal
if tight, the jar may be turned upside down for the
second
12 hours.
Pack
in
smaller
jars
and store in refrigerator.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Arrange bread slices on a baking sheet; place a slice of cheese on each bread slice.
Place in oven to melt cheese.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken pieces; cook until done.
Place 1 piece cooked chicken on top of each bread slice.
Return to oven to keep warm.
Pour wine into same skillet. Add mushrooms and onions; saute until cooked.
Stir in cornstarch, milk and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Place chicken-topped bread on a platter.
Top with mushroom sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Cut strawberries into slices.
Put a layer of Nilla wafers in a large bowl, then on top of the wafers, put a layer of strawberry slices.
Continue this layering between the two until you have filled the bowl, leaving at least 1 1/2 inches at the top of the bowl.

title: chicken kiev
directions: In a small bowl, combine margarine, garlic, chives and parsley; mix thoroughly.
Form into 3/4-inch thick roll on waxed paper; wrap.
Chill until very firm.
With a rolling pin, gently flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut chilled roll of margarine mixture in 6 portions.
Place 1 in center of each chicken breast half.
Roll up tightly, tucking in ends.
Secure with toothpicks.
Dip each in flour, dusting lightly, then in egg mixed with water, then in bread crumbs, until well coated.
Chill thoroughly.

title: mom's chocolate chip brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream together with electric mixer, shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well. By hand add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot and orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add carrots, cheese and pineapple.
Let stand until firm.

title: marinated beans
directions: Combine drained vegetables and onions.
Blend all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: dump bars
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour, salt, eggs, oil and vanilla together with a wooden spoon.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 cup walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips and walnuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Put in buttered casserole dish, after mixing together.
Crush 3/4 small box Ritz crackers.
Place on top of vegetables.
Add 1 package slivered almonds and 1 stick butter, sliced, on top evenly.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: In a bowl, mix together cinnamon and sugar.
Roll each biscuit in mixture.
Layer on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan as in fallen dominoes order with biscuits.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and ice cream. Bring to a soft boil.
Pour over biscuits. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Just dump together and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold
directions: Stir boiling water into jello; stir until dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon.
Pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours, or until thickened.
Reserve remaining cup at room temperature.
Stir apple and cranberry sauce into thickened jello.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold and refrigerate until set.
Beat reserved cup of gelatin and cream cheese with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour over gelatin in mold.
Let set until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Serves 12.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat cream of mushroom soup (undiluted) and cream cheese until smooth.
Add pepper, onion, gelatine and mayonnaise.
Fold in crab meat last.
Pour in mold and chill several hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In 2-quart pan, cook butter or margarine, cocoa, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil about 1 minute.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let harden.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Add enough additional flour to roll out.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick or pinch off dough and make into small balls.
Pat down to desired thickness.
They are softer if not rolled or patted too thin.
Bake at 300° until barely done.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add apples; stir to mix.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Very moist; no frosting required.

title: tv hash
directions: Mix all dry cereals and salted peanuts in a large roaster. Mix Worcestershire sauce and butter together and pour over cereal. Cover and cook in a slow oven at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine
brown	sugar,	oleo, corn syrup and salt; heat until bubbly,
then
cook for 5 minutes.	Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Stir until foamy and pour over the corn. Put the corn in 2 large baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: frosted cashew cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Add flour mixture and sour cream; stir.
Fold in cashews.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: ham and egg hash brown pie
directions: Lightly coat two 9 inch pie plates with non-stick cooking spray. Coarsely shred potatoes; place into a large bowl of cold water to keep them from discoloring and to rinse off excess starch.

Heat 2 tsp. oil in a large skillet. Drain half of the potatoes very well, add to skillet and sprinkle with 1/2 tsp. salt. Cook over medium high heat, stirring often, 8 minutes or until potatoes are soft and pale golden. Press potatoes evenly over bottom and up sides of pie plate. Repeat for second pie. Cover and refrigerate up to one day.

About 50 minutes before serving, heat oven to 350°. Whisk eggs, milk, dry mustard and remaining 1/4 tsp. salt in a large bowl to blend. Divide ham, cheese, bell pepper and scallions between pie plates. Pour half the eggs mixture over each.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until a knife inserted near center of pies comes out clean.

title: microwaved fish
directions: Arrange fish on a microwave-proof platter with the thicker parts to the outside of the dish. Combine other ingredients and brush mixture over fish. Cover fish with plastic wrap or wax paper and microwave on the High setting for 5 minutes. Check for doneness. Continue microwaving and checking at 1 minute intervals until fish is flaky and no longer translucent in the center. Garnish with 2 teaspoons lemon or lime peel and parsley. Yield: 4 servings.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Put pineapple juice, orange, lemon and sugar into blender and liquify.
Pour mixture over ice.

title: cheesy hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until slightly tender.
Drain and set aside. Brown meat and onion in small skillet.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Oil a 1-quart casserole and spoon in 1/3 of the meat mixture.
Add macaroni and then the rest of the meat mixture. Spread cheese on top and cover tightly.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Combine flour and cocoa.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add nuts and beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: chicken wing vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken wings until tender.
Remove wings from broth and add can of tomatoes and frozen soup mix.

(If you are making a large amount of soup, use large bag of frozen soup mix; if a small amount if being prepared, use a small bag of frozen soup mix.) Add potatoes (2 or 3 for small amount or 5 or 6 for larger amount).
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: ashley's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to the directions on the box.
As you stir the ingredients until well blended, be sure to take a taste test of the batter before spreading into the greased pan.
Leave a little in the bowl and on spatula to taste while the rest bakes.

title: snicker bars
directions: Melt chocolate bits and shortening in double boiler and stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and
pour
half
of
the mixture into foil-lined, 9-inch square pan and refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
Return remaining chocolate to double boiler to keep warm. Combine over boiling water the caramels, butter and water.
Stir until caramels and mixture
are smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into chocolate-lined pan
and	spread evenly.
Refrigerate until tacky, about 15 to 20
minutes.	Spread remaining	chocolate
evenly
on
top of caramel.	Refrigerate and
chill 1 hour.	Cut into 1 x 2-inch pieces.
Keep refrigerated.
Tastes just like Snickers.

title: one step cobbler
directions: Place fruit on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Mix together flour, salt, sugar, milk and egg.
Toss with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Drizzle butter over top and bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes until brown.

title: jailhouse rolls
directions: Mix yeast in lukewarm water; blend and set aside.
Mix potatoes, oleo, eggs, salt and sugar; blend into flour and add yeast water.
Blend well; place in greased bowl.
Cover with cold damp cloth and place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Remove amount of dough desired; roll out and cut.
Butter tops and let rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no-bake fruit cake
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring until they melt.
Remove from heat and pour over graham crackers, raisins, candied fruit and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Place in wax paper-lined pan.
Press down firmly.
Cover with foil. Place it into refrigerator and allow cake to "age" for 1 month. Uncover once weekly and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon brandy.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk, ReaLime juice and food coloring.
Pour into pastry shell and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Top with whipped topping.

title: mexican plum pies
directions: Halve and pit plums; sprinkle sugar over them in a saucepan until sugar is dissolved and juices are formed.
Bring to a boil and simmer until tender (10 minutes).
Allow to cool.
Butter tortillas on one side with sugar and cinnamon sprinkled on top; bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour liquid ingredients over dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch pan or muffin papers.
(Makes 12.)
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: red hot cinnamon apples
directions: Cook all but apples for 10 minutes.
Remove white part of candy centers.
Add apples and cook 10 minutes more.
Remove apples and cook syrup 5 minutes more.
Pour over apples and store in fridge.

title: sandwich treat
directions: Stir all together.
Spread on Italian rolls.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas cranberries
directions: Spread cranberries in iron skillet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cover.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.
Remove lid and pour brandy into skillet.
Serve from crystal compote.

title: pancakes
directions: Whisk all together.
Place small amount of oil in fry pan or on griddle.
Cook each side of pancake until golden brown.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Bring nectar to a boil.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Stir in water and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in oranges, grapes and apples.
Pour into a 4-cup mold.
Serves 6. Double recipe for a 7 1/2 x 11 x 2-inch pan.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange potatoes and 1 tablespoon of cut up onion evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread evenly over potatoes.
Juicy meat loaf bakes right over sliced potatoes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift together salt, sugar, cinnamon, flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to liquid ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans* and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese smoked ribs or chicken
directions: You will need 4 cups hickory or fruitwood chips.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all except cheese.
Preheat oven to 375° and grease large skillet.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in pan.
Add 1/2 cheese. Pour rest of mixture on top and add cheese.
Bake about 50 minutes.

title: sub salad
directions: Mix together the first six ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Chill.

title: tamale pie
directions: Heat butter and oil and saute onion and garlic until golden brown.
Add meat and brown slightly.
Put tomatoes, corn, salt and chili powder in pan and simmer for 20 minutes.
Let cool, then put with meat and pour into a shallow pan (10 x 14-inch).
Press olives into mixture.
Combine corn meal and milk with beaten eggs and spread with a spoon over filling.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: swedish tea-log
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water until dissolved.
In a bowl, stir flour, sugar and salt, then add oleo.
Blend together until thoroughly mixed.
Add milk and egg.
Mix egg in the milk, then the yeast mixture.
Stir yeast in the water (lukewarm).
Chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Roll like pie dough and sprinkle with nuts.
Roll into a roll.
Let rise for 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Layer broccoli with remaining ingredients and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased casserole dish.

title: fran's casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, put layer of potatoes, onions, meat and beans.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup and water over layers.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
To shorten baking time, parboil potatoes 15 minutes.

title: cold asparagus
directions: Cut off hard ends of asparagus; boil spears for 5 minutes. Place lettuce leaves on a dish.
Place pimientos over the lettuce (drain oil).
Place 5 asparagus spears on top of lettuce and pimiento.
Top asparagus with a clump of sprouts.
Chill in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Pour balsamic vinegar to taste over asparagus.
Sprinkle ground pepper to taste.

title: rasberry preserves
directions: Bring tomatoes and sugar to a boil; remove from heat and add gelatin.

title: stuffed camel
directions: Skin, trim and clean the camel, lamb and chickens.
Boil until tender.
Cook rice.
Fry nuts until brown; mix with rice. Hard-boil and peel eggs.
Stuff chickens with eggs and rice. Stuff camel with lamb and rice.
Boil in a large enough (this is important) oven until brown.
Spread the remaining mixed rice on a large tray; place camel on with eggs and nuts.
Serves 80 to 100 people.
Isn't that better than that T.V. dinner?

title: gingerbread-raisin scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Blend first 6 ingredients in a food processor.
Add butter and process until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Beat milk, egg, molasses and vanilla to blend in a large bowl.
Add flour mixture and raisins; stir gently until dough forms.
Gather dough into a ball.
On a lightly floured surface, press dough into a 1-inch thick round. Cut round into 8 wedges.
Place on prepared baking sheet.
Bake until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice with mixer. Blend in onions and chipped beef.
Shape combined ingredients into a ball.
Mince the onion tips.
Roll the ball in the tips.
Put in a plastic bowl and refrigerate for one day.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour until crumbly like pie dough.
Bake in small oblong pan at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat eggs slightly and then add sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and grated rind and juice of fresh lemon.
Cover baked crust with egg mixture and bake 20 minutes or until firm.
Sift powdered sugar over.

title: pasta alfredo
directions: Prepare the water for the fettuccine.
Bring cream and butter to a boil in a saute pan.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 30 seconds.
Add half the Parmesan, and a little freshly ground black pepper.
Whisk until smooth and remove from the heat.
Cook the fettuccine and add to the cream.
Add the rest of the Parmesan. Toss the noodles well in the sauce and serve immediately.
Garnish with more black pepper.

title: pineapple and cream cheese salad
directions: Heat sugar and juice over low heat.
Add gelatine which has been softened in cold water.
Chill until soft set.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs; add oil and vanilla.
Beat this, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves. Very good!

title: fruit dip appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with sliced fruit (apples, pears or strawberries) and gingersnap cookies, too.

title: b j's hermits
directions: Cream shortening with sugars.
Add eggs, but save 1 tablespoon to brush on the tops of the cookies.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquids.
Add nuts and raisins.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 3 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Can be frozen.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mash corned beef with a fork until smooth.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball and refrigerate.
Can be rolled in parsley or nuts.
Serve with a hard cracker.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Add salt, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce to the water.
Bring to rapid boil.
Slowly add the grits and boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup oleo and cheese.
Stir until oleo melts. Beat eggs.
Stir in milk.
Add grits mixture.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot top with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated crab salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and marinate overnight.
Toss with lettuce, cherry tomatoes and sliced fresh mushrooms, etc. before serving.

title: whole artichoke pickles
directions: Wash and scrape artichokes and let stand overnight in salt water (1 tablespoon salt to 1 quart water).
Drain; soak one day in alum water.
Rinse well.
Soak mustard seed in small amount of vinegar.
Boil rest of vinegar and spices a few minutes.
Let cool; add mustard and mustard seed.
Put artichokes in a crock; add liquid mixture.
Let stand at least a week before using.
Dip artichokes out as desired.
When supply is exhausted, more artichokes may be added to same liquid if liquid is heated.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator overnight. Also great with Bugles!

title: spicy steak fries
directions: In a large bowl, whisk egg whites and water.
Toss potato wedges into the egg mixture. In a large plastic bag, combine bread crumbs, paprika, salt, garlic powder and red pepper.
Shake well until all mixed together. Add potato wedges.
Shake until potato wedges are evenly coated.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake according to directions on potato package.
Serve hot with steak.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water; stir until blended.
Stir in 2 teaspoons of sugar; set aside.
Combine cottage cheese, onion, dill weed, baking powder, salt, 2 tablespoons sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Knead out on floured surface until smooth and elastic. Place dough in greased bowl; turn to bring greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place.
After dough has risen, divide and put in greased bread pans.
Let rise double.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 13 cake pan. Cook soup, sour cream, onion and cheese until creamy.
Pour over potatoes. Pour melted margarine on top. Put crumb mixture over potatoes. Bake 350° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and golden mushroom soup together with 1/2 can of water.
Pour over the chicken and bake for 50 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown meat, add onions, garlic, bell pepper, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cook 5 min.
Check seasoning now!
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with prepared cornbread batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese when you take it out of the oven. (Canned jalapeno may also be used as a garnish for a spicier dish.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potato until soft.
Mash, then add:
butter and vanilla. Put confectioners sugar in 1/3 cup at a time, until like pie crust.
Roll out; spread peanut butter on, roll up and put in freezer until firm (not frozen).
Then take out and cut in desired size.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate praline layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In small, heavy saucepan, combine butter, 1/4 cup whipping cream and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat just until butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Pour into two 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Sprinkle evenly with chopped pecans.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix flour and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Cover tightly to store.
Does not need refrigeration.
To make 8-inch pie crust, add 2 to 4 tablespoons ice water to 1 1/4 cups pie crust mix.
Mix gently and roll.
Adjust the amount of mix to the size of pie shell desired.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening in bowl; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition. Combine baking powder and flour; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat chicken and broth in covered pan over low heat until thoroughly hot.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and add celery, pimento, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine lemon juice with mayonnaise and pour over chicken mixture.
Toss lightly.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix everything together, flour last. Bake at 325° until done.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour over vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Drain well before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: chewies
directions: Cook approximately 25 minutes at 325°.
Shake down twice, first after 10 to 12 minutes, then about 10 minutes later.

title: jailhouse rolls
directions: Mix yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Mix hot potatoes with oleo, eggs, salt and sugar.
Add the lukewarm water with the yeast.
Add flour a little at a time and mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix well.
Make balls about the size of a quarter.
Bake at 350° for about 16 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: corned beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage just short of tender.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, draining well.
Add tomatoes and stir.
Sprinkle half of cheese onto top of cabbage and then stir in hash. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and then layer with bread crumbs or croutons.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
(This recipe also microwaves well.
After combining all ingredients, microwave on High for about 15 minutes.)

title: cinnamon basil whole wheat peach bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together all-purpose flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into large bowl.
Stir in whole wheat flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Make well in center and set mixture aside.
In medium bowl, whisk until blended mashed peach, milk, oil, egg and peach extract.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir just until moistened.
Fold in cinnamon basil.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 5 1/2 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until skewer inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: robyn's chicken salad
directions: Cover chicken with water; season to taste with salt, pepper and seasoned salt.
Cook until done; drain.
Cool and chop medium fine. Add chopped celery, chopped eggs, and pickles.
Blend with Miracle Whip and serve chilled on lettuce leaf or in a sandwich.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Used 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork slowly.
Add 1/4 c. water, cover and simmer until tender (about 1 hour).
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Pour over hot cooked pork.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onions.
Serve over noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add Karo and milk.
Bring to a boil, then cook on medium heat; stirring often until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 stick oleo, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 heaping tablespoons peanut butter (I use chunky peanut butter).
Beat until creamy.

title: rosie's chocolate frosting
directions: Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool and beat.

title: nana's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add flour to sugar in box.
Mix around; add to eggs and melt butter.
Add to mixture, also vanilla and pecans.
Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's zucchini cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add almonds and chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: argentinian stew in a pumpkin shell
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Cook meat, onion and garlic in oil until browned.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, salt, pepper, sugar, apricots, potatoes, sweet potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Beat
sugar,
pudding
and
milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip
until
creamy.
Add
2 drops yellow food coloring. Put
in a
9 x 13-inch pan or 3-quart baking dish.
Alternate graham crackers and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with graham crackers.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Heat canned frosting until
like syrup, then pour over graham crackers, then sprinkle with nuts. Chill 12 to 16 hours before serving.

title: homemade hot tamales
directions: Pressure cook chicken until done (save the broth).
After deboning chicken, mix with raw ground beef; cook slowly together over low heat until browned.
Add one chopped onion, chili powder, red pepper and salt to taste.
Mix corn meal (as making corn bread); spread over cut aluminum pieces, then spread meat mixture over the meal mixture.
Roll up; put in large pot and pour broth over it.
Boil until meal mixture is cooked.

title: no scorch caramels
directions: Mix sugar, salt, syrup and 1 cup cream in 2-quart pot.
Cook and stir 10 minutes (to boil). Add rest of cream slowly.
While stirring, continue to boil candy. Cook 5 minutes. Stir in butter, one teaspoon at a time, and cook to 248°.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Mix and stir.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cool. Turn out onto board and cut in squares. Wrap in waxed paper.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat; stir in onion soup mix, tomato sauce and water. Cover; simmer for 15 minutes. Alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, soda and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter.
Saute the onions until golden.
Add the potatoes, carrots, water, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes (or longer if you want the potatoes creamy).
Stir in the milk and parsley and heat until hot, but not boiling.
Stir in the potato flakes during the last few minutes of cooking.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese roll
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Chop garlic as fine as possible.
Mix cheese and garlic.
Add nuts.
Make into rolls the size of Hi-Ho crackers.
Roll in chili powder.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Mix ingredients and save 1 c. Spread rest of the batter in 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking dish.
Batter will be thick.

title: sooner-state beans with spareribs
directions: After looking, washing and draining beans, cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Cover pot and let stand for 1 hour.
Do not drain.
Meanwhile, cut spareribs into serving size pieces.
Brown lightly in heavy skillet lightly coated with olive oil.
Saute garlic after browning ribs.
Return ribs to skillet (or transfer ribs and garlic to large heavy pot and cover with water).
Simmer, covered, until ribs are tender.
Drain beans and pour into roasting pan.
Arrange spareribs on top of beans. Add water in which ribs have been cooked.
Season with salt, pepper, chili powder and ground cumin.
(Add garlic powder if not using fresh garlic.)
Arrange onion and peppers on top of ribs. Pour tomatoes over all.
Cover and bake in preheated slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.

title: diabetic pink salad
directions: Pour pineapple in large pan.
Add jello and cook over medium heat until jello is dissolved.
Set off heat and cool a few minutes.
Fold in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or bowl and refrigerate several hours.

title: blackberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nutmeg together in a large bowl.
Add rolled oats and mix well.
In another bowl, cream together butter and brown sugar. Set aside.
Beat eggs in a dish.
Add buttermilk to beaten eggs. Set aside.

title: tex-mex easy dinner
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Drain and add diced tomatoes, tomato paste, salt and pepper, beans and corn.
Add water.
Simmer over low heat for approximately 30 minutes.
Cook rice as directed.
Serve meat mix over hot rice. Top with picante sauce and jalapenos.
Some even like grated cheese on top.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Simmer olive oil, onion and pepper for 8 minutes. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes or until warm.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, and beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture. Place flour in large bowl, add dates, orange slices and nuts. Stir to coat each piece and add this mixture with coconut to creamed mixture.
Makes a very stiff dough.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: beef tenderloin ala madeira(serves 4)
directions: In a large saute pan, brown garlic in olive oil.
Remove when browned.
Lightly flour beef on all sides.
Place in olive oil and saute on both sides until browned.
Add sliced mushrooms to beef, along with basil, oregano, parsley and wine.
Cook until wine evaporates, then add water and butter.
Salt and pepper the mixture to taste.
Stir slightly and cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
(If rare beef is desired, take beef out after adding wine and add again after wine has evaporated.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package and allow to chill.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Mix the powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Combine the cream cheese and powdered sugar with the pudding and Cool Whip.
Stir until mixture is creamy.
Begin layering ingredients in a clean flower pot (small). Begin with a layer of Oreos, then the pudding mixture.
You may want to add gummy worms to the pudding as you layer.
Continue layering and end with a thick layer of Oreos.
You may want to put an artificial flower or plant in it to make it look real.
Serve the dirt cake with a garden spade.

title: apple fritters
directions: In medium bowl, combine 1 cup flour, granulated sugar and salt.
In small bowl, whisk milk and egg; then gradually whisk into dry ingredients until smooth.
Set aside.

title: chicken and cheese rollups
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/8 inch thickness.
Sprinkle with salt & pepper.
Place one slice of cheese on each breast.
Fold in sides of breasts and roll up, securing with wood toothpicks.
Roll chicken in flour, then egg, then breadcrumbs.
Place in baking dish and and bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
In saucepan, mix broth, butter and parsley.
Heat until butter is melted and pour over chicken.
Bake another 10 minutes, remove toothpicks and serve.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Cool.
Stir in cheese, egg, crumbs and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook shells in salted boiling water about 15 minutes.
Run cold water over them; drain.
Lay on paper towels.
Spoon some sauce over bottom of pan.
Place stuffed shells on top and pour rest of sauce over.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until casserole is brown and bubbly.

title: layered chocolate dreams
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a pan over low heat.
Stir until butter is melted.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Remove from heat and pour into an 8-inch square pan, patting into an even sheet.
Cover with filling.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake cake per instructions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding per instructions.
Mix cream cheese into pudding.
Put on cooled cake.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Put on top of pudding mixture on cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: hot chocolate milk mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
Mix 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup mix.

title: jelly filled cookies
directions: Combine.
Roll out on board and cut, putting jelly on one and another cookie on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: self crust cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Put into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven.
Leave cheese cake in hot oven for 1 more hour.
(Do not open door.) Remove from oven.
Cool for 2 or 3 hours.
Top with favorite topping or leave plain.
Canned pie filling, chilled, makes a good topping.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: *Bake cake mix according to directions and use 1/2 of cake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup and milk in a greased casserole.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with onion rings.
Return to oven; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: coffee chocolate custard
directions: Pour over chocolate the strong hot coffee.
Add the milk, sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
blend in blender.
Bake at 300° to 325° until knife is clean, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed ground beef
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Make six patties and put 1/4 cup of stuffing in center of each.
Draw meat around stuffing and seal.
Place in ovenproof casserole.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Pan-fry onion
in
fat	(hot)
in a heavy skillet.
Add ground beef;
brown
thoroughly.	Combine
meat,	seasonings, noodles and
soup in a 3-quart casserole with cover.
Top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crab in pastry casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Add mushrooms and spinach; mix well.
Add cheese, bread crumbs and soup.
Mix well.
Gently add crabmeat.
Let mixture cool.
Add in beaten eggs.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Put in gallon jar.
Add salt, pickling spice and alum. Fill the jar with vinegar.
Seal and let set for 3 months.
Pour off solution (do not keep).
Slice cucumbers.
Put in large container. Add the sugar. Stir well.
Let set for 24 hours.
(Sugar will make canning solution.)
Put in jars and seal. Can be kept in refrigerator.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Combine milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Layer bananas, wafers and pudding, ending with pudding.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until smooth and forms together.
Stir in milk, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute until thick.
Stir in crabmeat.
Fill mushrooms and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until slightly brown on top.

title: chili rellenos won ton appetizers(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine beef, onions, cheese, oregano, cumin, garlic salt and chilies.
Place a spoonful of the meat mixture on each won ton wrapper and follow package directions for folding and sealing.

title: chicken italiano
directions: In medium frying pan, heat oil.
Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add chicken and cook until lightly browned and tender.
Add stewed tomatoes and wine and cook over low heat until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.

title: quick and easy apple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and water together.
Add spices.
Stir in apple pie filling and nuts.

title: my chicken stuff
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Chop chicken into small pieces. Cook rice.
Add chicken to rice, chestnuts, chicken soup, mushroom soup and celery.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Keep adding sugar until smooth and stiff.
Form small balls the size of buckeyes or large marbles.
Place in single layer on pan and chill.

title: ras-cran supreme
directions: Mix and chill until firm.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat real well, oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 regular loaves or 2 layers.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes, but do not add milk.
Combine ingredients and put in casserole, greased with butter.
Sprinkle heavily with grated Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter; refrigerate overnight. Take out 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until top is golden brown.

title: oriental peanut chicken
directions: Soften peanut butter in microwave.
Mix with soy sauce. Spread on the outside of chicken.
Roast chicken at 400° for 1 hour.

title: golden gate lasagna
directions: Saute onion and beef in oil.
Add minced garlic, pepper, salt, oregano, parsley, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix the cake, oil, and eggs for 3 minutes.
Add oranges. Pour into 3 round metal pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Cool and place on wax paper.
Top with icing.

title: ham stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook the ham in hot oil about 3 minutes or until heated through, turning once.
Remove from skillet and drain fat from skillet.
In same skillet, combine water, onion, mushrooms, catsup, parsley, bouillon granules and dill weed. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until onion is tender.

title: skillet stir-fry
directions: In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil and add meat to brown. As it browns, add sauces. As meat is half cooked, add vegetables and mushrooms. Put a lid on it and cook on medium-high heat until sauce is thickened and vegetables are tender. Serve over rice.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Bring 4 quarts water to boil and add sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes. Make 8 cups tea and mix together with sugar water.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients except ginger ale.
Add this when ready to serve.
Pour over ice.
Makes 3 1/2 gallons.
Serves 100. This recipe may be divided in half.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl mix all fruit together, using the juices from the pineapple and oranges only (use all of it).
Mix the two juices, then add enough to the jello to be able to pour over the fruit mixture; mix.
Then add enough juice to the pudding mix to pour and pour over fruit; then mix.
Pour rest of juice over fruit; then mix.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat 5 egg whites to form soft peaks; set aside.
Beat 5 egg yolks and 1 whole egg until foamy.
Add vanilla and lemon extract. Slowly add sugar and beat well.
Slowly add flour and beat well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a well floured cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Invert on dish towel sprinkled with sugar.
Roll up for about 1 minute; unroll and spread with jelly.
Re-roll.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
