directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Drop onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add egg, milk, salt, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup crumbs, chopped Heath bars and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May substitute butter brickle bits and chocolate chips for Heath bars.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Steam broccoli slightly (optional).
Blend soup, cheese and egg.
Add mayo and milk; stir in broccoli.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with buttered crumbs.
(Parmesan cheese is also yummy.)
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Combine raspberries, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Mix together vanilla wafers, sugar and margarine.
Spread 2 1/2 cups of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend together cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over wafer mixture.
When raspberry mixture is cool, spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crushed wafers over top.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine all other ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: tomato soup dressing(makes about 1 quart)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until mixed. Refrigerate.
It will keep about 4 weeks.

title: momma teegarden's "beer cheese"
directions: Measure beer and let sit out 8 to 12 hours.
Mix together with fork, adding beer to suit consistency (like a thick cake batter). Pour into mason jars.
Refrigerate.
Serve with saltine crackers. The longer this is refrigerated, the hotter it gets!!

title: patsy's spicy pickles(yields 3 quarts)
directions: Pour boiling water over fresh whole cucumbers and let stand 12 hours.
Drain and wash cucumbers and slice as you desire.
Pack slices into hot jars.
Bring vinegar solution mixture to a boil and pour over pickles in jar and seal.
Put jars in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: ham skillet dinner
directions: Place ham with liquid in 10-inch skillet; break up with fork. Add noodles, sauce mix, broccoli, water and onion.
Heat to boiling over high heat, stirring occasionally; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring frequently, until desired consistency 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with Crunchy Topping.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt, sugar, vanilla and rind together.
Heat butter in frying pan.
Have egg mixture in shallow flat dish.
Soak bread mixture and brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup or powdered sugar.

title: deep fry batter
directions: In small bowl, lightly mix together cold water and egg.
Add 1 cup cake flour.
Barely mix just enough to dampen.
(Batter should be lumpy.)
Then add 2/3 cup more flour.
Sprinkle it over batter and fold in twice.
Dip small strips of fish, chicken or turkey in batter.
(Kind of pull them through the batter to coat.)
Cook in hot oil until golden.
Drain.
Keep warm in oven.

title: slaw to freeze
directions: Make a syrup of vinegar, water, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar.
Boil one minute.
Let syrup stand until lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage and freeze in containers.

title: cheese ravioli asparagus pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs with a fork.
Stir in undiluted soup and pepper until blended.
Cover bottom of pan with a single layer of ravioli.
Spoon 1/3 of soup mixture over ravioli.
Top with 1/2 of the zucchini, tomatoes, basil and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and 1/3 of soup mixture. Bake for 45 minutes, or until center is set and browned on top. Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add
rest of ingredients and chill 4 hours.
Shape into ball or log.
Roll in pecans.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and shred.
Place half the tortillas in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken atop.
In large mixing bowl combine soups, salsa, onion and bouillon water.
Mix well.
Place other half of tortillas on top of chicken.
Cover with soup mixture.
Top with cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: peach fluff
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Refrigerate until set.
Soften cream cheese.
Drain peaches.
Puree peaches until smooth.
Add cream cheese to peaches and beat until smooth.
Add the set jello and beat until smooth.
Spoon into Cool Whip.
Stir until well blended.
Chill.
Enjoy.

title: chicken casino
directions: In flat dish, press bread crumbs into pieces of chicken on both sides.
Reserve.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except the bacon. Place in a two-quart casserole. Lay bacon on top. Bake uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bacon is cooked. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: black cherry dessert
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple; save juice. Heat juice for liquid for jello.
Pour cherries and pineapple into bowl and then dissolved jello, then soft drink.
Mix well. Place nuts on top. Refrigerate to jell.

title: red punch
directions: Mix and chill first 4 ingredients.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: five cup salad
directions: Toss together and chill overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Place maraschino cherry in center of each serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Make into ball; roll in nuts, if desired.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: aunt sally's blueberry pie
directions: Mix berries, sugar and flour together (works well in a plastic bag); mix gently as to not break berries; empty into a deep-dish pie crust.
Take the second crust and cut into strips.
Form a lattice effect on top of the pie.
Pat margarine at 2-inch intervals on top of the crust.
Bake at 375° until pie crust is brown.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain well.
Add onion, chili powder, 1 can salsa and 1 cup of water, mixing well.
Simmer until liquid is evaporated.
Warm tortillas. Place spoonful of meat mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll to enclose filling.
Place in baking dish.
Pour remaining salsa and enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Top with cheese; bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 7 minutes.

title: maple chews
directions: Cream all but the flour together.
Gradually add flour until all together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat the cooking oil in medium skillet.
Hold tortillas with tongs. Dip each in hot oil 5 to 10 seconds or until limp. Drain on paper towels. Add oil as needed.
Combine chillies, onion, chicken and salsa.
Spoon on tortillas.
Roll up.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover and spread on sour cream. Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: great bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bread (both sides).
Cook 25 minutes at 350° or until brown and bubbly.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add can of cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and cream cheese.
While still hot, stir and mix well.
Put into jello mold or Pyrex dish.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer sauerkraut.
Over that, spread a layer of noodles.
In a bowl, mix soup with milk, onions and mustard and pour over the noodles.
Next, arrange a layer of sliced smoked sausage and then a layer of sliced Swiss cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with margarine and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: calzone
directions: Let thawed dough rise.
Roll out dough in rectangular form. Mix spinach, Parmesan cheese, oil, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Spread mixture on rolled out dough.
Layer meats and cheese.
Roll dough like a jelly roll.
Brush with egg and cheese.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Make diagonal slashes on top, not cutting through dough. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Slice and serve with a salad.

title: delicious spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; add onion and bell pepper.
Add rest of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes or longer.
Add water, if necessary.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: alaska logs
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 40 minutes.
Cut in 1/2 x 2-inch bars. Roll in finely granulated sugar to form logs and to coat.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add sugar and pineapple syrup. Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, oil, salt, sugar and water.
Mix well.
Let dough stand 30 minutes.
Knead dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Make split in center of circle.
Fry dough in oil. Brown on both sides.
Drain on towels.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, pinching edges together to seal.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes and cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayo and salad dressing mix; beat until well blended.
Spread mixture over crust.
Sprinkle with cheese and vegetables.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into 1 x 1 1/2-inch bites.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: cucumber-onion dip
directions: Blend with mixer all ingredients except cucumber and onions until smooth.
Stir cucumber and onions into mixture with spoon. Mix well and then chill for several hours.
Serve chilled with chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all together. Add enough milk to make thick, so it will drop from spoon. Drop in hot grease. Cook until brown.

title: yams and apples
directions: Melt and mix butter, sugar and brandy or sherry.
Pour sauce over layer of yams, sauce, layer of apples and sauce in a well buttered long baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed spaghetti squash
directions: Place the squash, cut side down, in a baking dish and add 1/2-inch of water.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until the squash is fork-tender.

Place the halves on a plate. Fluff the strands with a fork. During the last 10 minutes of baking time, heat the zucchini, tomato juice, oregano, beans, garlic, salt and pepper in a medium saucepan. Spoon the mixture into the spaghetti squash halves and toss lightly.

title: house slaw
directions: In large bowl, make layers of cabbage, pepper and onions. Sprinkle sugar over top.
In saucepan, combine mustard, sugar, celery seed, salt, vinegar and oil.
Bring to full boil while stirring.
Pour over slaw.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 4 hours (overnight is better).
To serve, toss salad.

title: fruited sweet sour pork
directions: Melt butter and saute meat until brown.
Drain pineapple, reserve juice.
Combine juice, Russian dressing, water, cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar and salt.
Pour over meat and stir until thick.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes, until meat is tender.
Add green peppers, onions and pineapple.
Cook about 5 minutes and serve over hot cooked rice.

title: party punch for 65
directions: Mix juices. Add 5 bottles of ginger ale to juices, place orange slices and frozen cherry ice cubes into punch as floaters.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour in a heavy saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into the beaten yolks.
Then blend yolks into hot mixture in saucepan. Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla; cool, stirring occasionally.
Just before pouring into pie shell, fold in coconut.
Chill thoroughly, about 2 hours.
Serve, topped with whipped cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Put butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and melt in oven.
Mix all other ingredients together except peaches.
Pour batter into melted butter, will be thin.
Then place peach slices around in batter; do not stir.
Pour on juice.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake in oven about 30 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: chicken kurma
directions: Heat the oil and then add onion and garlic.
Saute until browned.
Add the chicken yogurt and spices together.
Add about 1 cup of water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for about 1 hour. Lower heat and cook until most of the water dries out and the chicken is tender.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour (or until done).
Let cool. Cut into cubes and set aside.
Melt butter or margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Add potato cubes, pepper, green onions, bacon and cheese. Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add extra milk, if necessary, for desired thickness.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, melt butter, add peppers, onions, celery and garlic.
Stir and cook 10 minutes.
Add crawfish, shrimp or chicken, half and half and cheese.
Stir and cook on low until cheese melts.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine fettuccine and cheese sauce. Pour into 3-quart casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: 125 year old party pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until very light.
Add whole eggs one at a time.
Add flavoring and beat again.
Add flour, mixed with baking powder.
Alternate with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour in tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cheddar-pecan cheese ball
directions: Bring Cheddar and cream cheese to room temperature.
In medium mixing bowl, beat cheeses, sour cream, mustard and onion powder with mixer until well combined.
Apply seal and refrigerate several hours.
Shape in ball.
Arrange pecan halves around base. Coat ball with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate up to 1 week.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving.
Serve with breadsticks or assorted crackers.

title: company potatoes
directions: Quarter, peel and boil potatoes until tender.
In the meantime, in greased, 2-quart baking dish, mix all other ingredients, except reserved cheese, and soup mixture gently.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: no-roll pie shell
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pie pan.
Combine oil and milk in measuring cup.
Whip with fork and pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix with fork until flour is completely dampened.
Press evenly and firmly with fingers to line bottom of pan, then press dough up to line sides and partly cover rim.
Be sure dough is pressed to uniform thickness.
To flute, pinch dough lightly with fingers.
Do not use a high fluted edge.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth. Chill before serving. Serve dressing over salad greens. Yield: about 6 1/2 cups.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add pineapple chunks, juice and all, and milk.
Mix well.
Add bread (white, wheat or French).
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: brownies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Add dry ingredients; beat well with spoon.
Spread in greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Top with some of the noodles.
Bake, covered, for about 45 minutes, then uncovered for about 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: gingered salmon
directions: In glass or stainless-steel shallow bowl, large enough to hold salmon steaks in a single layer, combine teriyaki sauce, sherry, lemon juice and ginger root.
Add salmon and turn to coat with marinade.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight, turning fish occasionally.

title: hold your hat texas red chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, fry the suet until crisp.
Add steak cubes and brown.
Add seasonings and water.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Skim off fat.
Stir in cornmeal and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with pinto beans or cornbread.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beer cheddar soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, saute carrots, onions and celery in margarine until tender.
In blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade, combine vegetable mixture with 3/4 cup of the milk; puree.
Return mixture to saucepan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Blend flour into vegetable mixture.
Stir in remaining milk, broth and beer; cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Garnish as desired.
Yields 7 (1-cup) servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients. Cook in ungreased pan for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Combine lard, sugar, salt and milk in saucepan; warm to melt lard.
Cool to lukewarm and beat in egg.
Dissolve yeast in warm water
and add to milk mixture.
Add flour a cup at a time, beating
after each addition.
Do all this in a covered casserole dish.
Grease top of dough ball and cover.	Store in refrigerator overnight.	Make into clover leaf rolls by making 1-inch
balls and putting 3 in each greased muffin tin.
Cover and let rise about an hour.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until done. Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen rolls.

title: texas red chili
directions: In a large kettle, brown hamburger, one pound at a time. Remove after each cooking and set aside.
When last meat is cooked, return other browned meat to kettle. Add all other ingredients except corn meal and water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer with kettle covered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Mix corn meal and water together in a cup and add to kettle.
Simmer another 20 to 30 minutes.
Can add or delete spices to taste.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: I usually add nutmeg and ginger.

title: chicken and apple-pecan stuffing
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry. Place in a crock-pot. Melt butter in a skillet over medium-low heat and saut onion, celery, apple and raisins. Add pecans, water, applesauce, cream of chicken soup and stuffing mix; mix together. Spoon over chicken in the crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry danish
directions: Crumble angel food cake in pan.
Mix 8 ounces of Cool Whip with cake and press into pan.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
After mixing thoroughly, add 10 ounces Cool Whip and mix together.
Spread this on top of the cake mixture.
In a bowl, combine strawberries and glaze.
Pour over the cake and cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: up-side down german chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo in long pan, add coconut and pecans.
Prepare cake mix according to direction on box.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamy.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: cracker jills
directions: Mix well and chill at least 2 hours.
Shape into small balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: baked flounder
directions: Arrange fillets
in
a	lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle
with
onion, salt and pepper.
Combine apple juice
and lemon juice;
pour over fish.
Cover and bake at 350° for
25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Transfer
fish to serving platter.	Strain and reserve 2/3
cup
liquid.
Melt
butter in heavy saucepan over low	heat; add
flour,
stirring
until
smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add
whipped cream and save 2/3 cup liquid.
Cook over
medium
heat,
stirring
until thick. Pour over fish. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix chili sauce and grape jelly in a large saucepan.
Mix meat, onion flakes and garlic powder.
Form meatballs.
Put in a saucepan and cover; simmer for 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cobbler
directions: Put butter in baking dish and melt.
Add sugar and milk in another bowl and stir in flour and baking powder.
Put in baking dish and add fruit on top and bake at 375° until top is brown, about 40 minutes.
Batter will be thin when you put it in a baking dish to cook.
This is a small dish.

title: roasted turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brush the turkey with melted butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place skin side up on a rack on a shallow roasting pan, 20 minutes of roasting time per pound. Roast, uncovered, basting occasionally, with the rest of butter mixed with wine.
Let stand the roasted turkey for a few minutes before carving.
Cut into thin slices.
It can be served warm with a Bearnaise sauce or cold with a sauce made up of half sour cream and half mayonnaise and parsley.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to platter. Add chives, onions, lemon juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, stirring constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Add remaining butter and oil.
Stir.
Serves 4.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning and follow package directions.
Put crust in pan.
Spoon sauce on top.
Add hamburger mixture.
Put lettuce on top followed by tomatoes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese is bubbly and crust is brown.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: nora june truitt's ham loaf
directions: Mix jelly and chicken broth together.
Mix all into a loaf and bake in skillet with a lid on it for 1 hour.
When done, put a topping of brown sugar creamed with mustard (4 tablespoons of each) over the top and brown at 350° to 400°.

title: dianna's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 3 hours.

title: wassail
directions: Break cinnamon stick into smaller pieces.
Tie with 6 whole cloves and allspice in a cheesecloth bag.
Stud two oranges with five cloves each.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook slightly in unsalted water.
Mix together rest of ingredients until smooth.
Add carrots to mixture.
Marinate in refrigerator 3 to 4 days, stirring occasionally.

title: taco salad
directions: Warm chili.
Crush
corn chips over salad.
Spoon chili over chips.
Sprinkle grated cheese over chili.
Pour Catalina dressing and salsa on top.
Garnish with sour cream, tomatoes, olives and green onions.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash. Add onion, butter, spices and cheese. Simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Put in casserole dish. Cover lightly with bread crumbs or cracker crumbs. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: piroshki appetizers
directions: Cook onion in butter until lightly browned. Combine chicken, eggs, parsley, dill and enough sour cream to moisten slightly.

title: brown stew
directions: Brown meat in oil. Stir in next 12 ingredients. Cover and simmer for 2 hours. Add vegetables and cook until tender.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add water slowly, stirring to dissolve ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter; remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add beaten egg yolk, rind and juice of lemon and mix well.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Brown in slow oven.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Top with onion rings, mushrooms, bacon and mandarin oranges.
Set aside.
Heat sugar, oil, vinegar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce over low heat until sugar melts, but don't cook.
Pour dressing over spinach mixture just before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut butter into oats, sugar, flour, salt and spices until crumbly.
Spread pie filling in pie pan or square baking dish. Sprinkle crisp topping over pie filling and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Blend together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Add to mixture and spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on powdered sugared tea towel (cotton).
Roll towel and cake together.
Let cool 1/2 hour, then unroll and fill with mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla. Add to cake and re-roll.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: sandy's cajun cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients in food chopper and roll into logs.
Roll logs in chili powder.
Serve with crackers.

title: kartoffelsalat(hot potato salad)
directions: Peel potatoes and slice paper thin.
Saute bacon slowly in a frypan, then drain on paper towels.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Grease a large baking pan.
Mix together spaghetti sauce, onion and green pepper; set aside.
Mix together cottage or Ricotta cheese and egg; set aside.
Layer noodles, sauce, cheese mixture and Mozzarella until ingredients are used up.
Bake until brown and bubbly.

title: hidden valley ranch party pinwheels
directions: Heat oil in a medium size, nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onion, zucchini and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes or until tender. Add tomato and next 3 ingredients; cook 1 minute.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of Tillamook or Cheddar cheese over each bread half; top each half with 1/2 cup vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup Tillamook or Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese evenly over vegetable mixture.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Yields 2 servings.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix to make a smooth consistency.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg.
Blend these dry ingredients into the canned mixture, adding milk slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in. Fold in chopped, blanched almonds, figs and raisins.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: nannie's chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients (coffee last); batter is thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: black beans, corn and tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: In large saucepan, combine the black beans and enough cold water to cover them by 2 inches.
Add the 1 tablespoon olive oil, chopped onion and black pepper.
Bring the water to a boil and simmer the beans for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until they are just tender, but not mushy.
Drain the beans.
In a bowl, combine them with the corn, tomato, scallions, minced coriander and green chilies.

title: pasta salad a la greque
directions: Thoroughly rinse the artichoke hearts and let drain at least 15 minutes.
Place dressing, herbs and garlic in the bowl of a food processor equipped with a steel blade and process until herbs and garlic are finely chopped.
(Optional:
Herbs and garlic can be finely chopped by hand and whisked into dressing.)
Pour dressing into a large bowl.
Add the drained artichokes and let marinate for at least an hour, or overnight.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Melt chocolate chips and spread on top. Cool and cut into squares.

title: white chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 8-inch square baking pan; set aside. Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; set aside. Beat eggs in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed 30 seconds. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed, about 4 minutes until very thick and lemon-colored. Beat in chocolate mixture and vanilla. Beat in flour and salt at low speed just until blended. Stir in baking bar pieces and walnuts, if desired. Spread batter evenly into prepared baking pan. Bake 30 minutes or until edges just begin to pull away from sides of pan and center is set. Remove pan to wire rack. Cool.

title: lisa's vegetable chowder
directions: Saute vegetables in butter with thyme and bay leaves until tender (approximately 10 minutes).
Add chicken broth; simmer 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Remove 2 1/2 cups and puree in blender.
Hold hand firmly on top of blender when blender is turned on or let the 2 1/2 cups of the mixture cool down!
Enjoy.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix by hand.
Add water, about 1 1/2 tablespoons, if necessary.
Form into 3/4-inch balls and roll in granular sugar.
Sugar can be colored for the holidays.
Store in sealed containers so the rum does not evaporate.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put in large ovenproof bowl.
Put in carrots and peas.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Cover and cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine the cheeses, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and onion powder.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in dried beef, then in parsley.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or thinly sliced breads.
Makes 3 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in uncovered 8 x 10-inch dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in large bowl with sugar.
Pour over enough boiling water to cover.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
This is also a good light dessert.
It keeps well.

title: eight egg pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a large mixer bowl for 5 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 2 minutes after each addition.
Add flour gradually; beat for 5 minutes longer.
Stir in lemon extract and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cook at 300° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Wonderful!

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 1 stick oleo (melted) and press into long cake pan. Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick oleo on high speed for 15 minutes. Pour over crumbs. Split bananas lengthwise and place over mixture. Drain pineapple well and spread over bananas. Spread Cool Whip. Sprinkle chopped pecans and cherries over Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put hamburger into 9 x 13-inch pan, about 1-inch thick.
Add onion soup mix and cream of mushroom soup.
Layer Tater Tots on top.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Add sliced cheese to cover all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat uncooked ground meat into casserole dish.
Sprinkle minced onion on top of meat.
Smooth undiluted soup over all.
Layer Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix egg white with 2 tablespoons water.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in a separate bowl.
Coat pecans in egg white; spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle well with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Turn once.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble meat,
rice and soup mix.
Blend water with the mushroom soup.
Mix and put onion blades on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hungry boy's casserole
directions: Combine meat, celery, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper in skillet and fry until meat is no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in flat baking dish and top with canned biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are nicely browned.

title: spinach with cream cheese
directions: Cook and chop spinach.
Drain slightly.
Add crumbled cream cheese, melted butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Reheat and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; add milk.
Cook over medium heat in saucepan until reaches soft boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat with mixer several minutes.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: meat crescents
directions: In skillet, brown meat with onion soup mix.
Lower heat and stir in Cheddar cheese, then turn off heat.
Press open crescent rolls on a cookie sheet (one at a time) and place 1 tablespoon in center of dough and fold like a diaper.
Put in 325° oven until golden brown.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix cream cheese with fruit.
Add coconut and marshmallows to taste.
Can add more of any ingredient to stretch the amount.

title: potato pancakes(rievkooche or reibekuchen)
directions: Measure water into a large bowl and add lemon juice.
Grate raw potatoes into the bowl filled with water (the lemon juice should help prevent the potatoes from turning brown).

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil, then remove from heat. Add 6 ounces (1 cup) Nestle semi-sweet real chocolate morsels and vanilla extract.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Transfer to a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 cup Nestle semi-sweet real chocolate morsels and the nuts.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Makes 16 (2 1/4-inch) squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; set aside.
Precook zucchini 10 minutes (do not overcook).
Place zucchini into a greased deep casserole dish (one layer).
Alternate layers with ground beef.
Add Spanish rice, pimiento and onion.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add grated cheese on top.
Place back in oven for 5 minutes. Garnish with paprika and parsley.
Will serve 8 to 10 people.

title: hummingbird nectar mix
directions: In a quart jar, combine all ingredients.
Shake to dissolve sugar. Add a few drops red food coloring.
Let cool and place in bird feeder.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan, cook over low heat until mixture boils.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool until firm.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans and bake.
When cool, split into 4 layers.
Blend sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill. Take 1 cup sour cream mixture and set aside.
Spread rest between layers.
Blend remaining cup of mixture with Cool Whip.
Spread on top and sides. Seal in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.
Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: lasagna
directions: Chop all vegetables. Saute in butter. Set aside. Brown meat and drain. Combine vegetables, meat, tomato sauce and all spices; simmer while noodles cook. Cook noodles with 1/8 cup of oil so noodles won't stick. Grease 13 x 9 pan. Layer all ingredients (noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan). Top with parsley, olives and Parmesan. Bake 20 minutes.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs and milk.
Sift flour, cornstarch, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; add mincemeat. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Layer the cheese mixture and
other ingredients.
Top with chopped green bell peppers, green onions, tomatoes and black olives.
Chill and serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: quick sugar cookies
directions: Mix in a bowl with wooden spoon.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients (prepare tomatoes as for canning). Cook to desired thickness.
Pour into jars; seal under pressure for 20 minutes.

title: zesty mexican cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower florets; drain and set aside.
Combine sauce ingredients in large saucepan and cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add cooked cauliflower and corn. Toss well and serve.
Serves 6.

title: devonshire pudding
directions: Bring milk, butter and sugar to a boil and pour on small pieces of bread; add beaten egg yolks and stiffly beaten egg whites. Place the mixture in a dish or bowl and bake at 350° for about an hour. (When baking place dish or bowl in a pan of water.)

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, let's get started.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup and spoons.
Check rum again.
It must be just right!!
To be sure the rum is of the highest quality, pour 1 level cup into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.
With electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of thugar and beat again.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Drain and remove stems from mushrooms, using a teaspoon to scoop out the stem.
In a mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Fill the center of each crown with a spoonful of stuffing.
Place on a greased shallow baking pan; brush with some melted butter.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes or until hot and lightly browned.
Serve in a chafing dish to keep mushrooms very hot. Makes approximately 24.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and milk in a small mixing bowl at medium speed with mixer until blended well.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water, then 3 cups hot water.
Let set.
Cut in small squares.

title: cup of macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni with salt, pepper and butter until done.
Pour in tomatoes.
Cover and let stand until dinner is ready.
This is Gracie's own dish.

title: smothered eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and soak in salted water for 20 minutes.
Drain. Heat oil and add eggplant, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper. Cook, covered, on low fire until tender.
(I like to eat this with a little rice.)

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except M&M's.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 3-inches apart, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 or 4 candies (M&M's) on top of each cookie.
Bake until lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: seven-up salad(a dessert-type salad)
directions: Add Jell-O to hot applesauce.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 7-Up and stir well.
Chill until thickened, stirring occasionally. Pour into mold that has been rinsed with cold water.
Chill well.

title: bobbie's icebox fruitcake
directions: Combine margarine, melted marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Combine other ingredients with cracker crumbs.
Combine the two mixtures and pack into buttered pans.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken until just tender; remove from bones (have at least 2 cups or more).
Cook the broccoli until just tender.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish the broccoli and chicken.
Mix the soups and mayonnaise; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Grate the cheese and spread on top.
Top with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and add milk.
Slowly add remaining ingredients and heat through.
Will thicken when cool.
Heat to serve.
Good make ahead and reheated.
Serve with taco chips.
